INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (446001, 'Seeing that our thirst was increasing and the water was killing us, while the storm did not abate, we agreed to trust to God, Our Lord, and rather risk the perils of the sea than wait there for certain death from thirst.', 71377, 0), (446002, 'I have no fear of death. More important, I don''t fear life.', 71412, 0), (446003, 'You can''t reconcile being pro-life on abortion and pro-death on the death penalty.', 4251, 0), (446004, 'The two great risks are risking too much but also risking too little. That''s for each person to decide. For me, not risking anything is worse than death. By far.', 30158, 0), (446005, 'Watching a peaceful death of a human being reminds us of a falling star one of a million lights in a vast sky that flares up for a brief moment only to disappear into the endless night forever. ', 1080, 0), (446006, 'If you think aficionados of a living Constitution want to bring you flexibility, think again. You think the death penalty is a good idea? Persuade your fellow citizens to adopt it. You want a right to abortion? Persuade your fellow citizens and enact it. That''s flexibility.', 21037, 0), (446007, 'There should be weeping at a man''s birth, not at his death.', 48659, 0), (446008, 'Marriage is almost as old as dirt, and it was defined in the garden between Adam and Eve. One man, one woman for life till death do you part. So I would never attempt to try to redefine marriage. And I don''t think anyone else should either. So do I support the idea of gay marriage? No, I don''t.', 1949, 0), (446009, 'If my survival caused another to perish, then death would be sweeter and more beloved.', 5542, 0), (446010, 'Some people hate funerals. I find them comforting. They hit the pause button on life and remind us that it has an end. Every eulogy reminds me to deepen my dash, that place on the tombstone between our birth and our death.', 37774, 0), (446011, '''Death at an Early Age'' was about racial segregation in Boston. ''Illiterate America'' was about grownups who can''t read. ''Rachel and Her Children'' was about people who were homeless in the middle of Manhattan.', 11500, 0), (446012, 'Death can never kill an idea. Ideas are more powerful than death. Ideas outlive men and can never be destroyed.', 11162, 0), (446013, 'If I die a violent death, as some fear and a few are plotting, I know that the violence will be in the thought and the action of the assassins, not in my dying.', 2002, 0), (446014, 'My character and good name are in my own keeping. Life with disgrace is dreadful. A glorious death is to be envied.', 20802, 0), (446015, 'In an artwork you''re always looking for artistic decisions, so an ashtray is perfect. An ashtray has got life and death.', 30824, 0), (446016, 'I couldn''t have foreseen all the good things that have followed my mother''s death. The renewed energy, the surprising sweetness of grief. The tenderness I feel for strangers on walkers. The deeper love I have for my siblings and friends. The desire to play the mandolin. The gift of a visitation.', 1709, 0), (446017, 'Religion provides the only story that is fundamentally consoling in the face of the worst possible experiences - the death of a parent, for instance. In fact, many religions take away the problem entirely, because their adherents ostensibly believe that they''re going to be reunited with everyone they love, and death is an illusion.', 1816, 0), (446018, 'Puerto Ricans who find they can no longer afford to keep their pets often choose to drop their dogs, sometimes even whole litters of puppies, at a beach - sometimes under cover of night, in secret - rather than surrender the animal to a city or state-run shelter where the animals will face grim conditions and almost certain death by euthanasia.', 67016, 0), (446019, 'Everything about aging in my experience so far has been a plus. Except the death part!', 1739, 0), (446020, 'The sinner who suddenly realizes God''s love for him and then looks at his rejection of that love feels a loss similar to the death of a loved one. A deep void is created in the soul and a loneliness akin to the agony of death.', 9130, 0), (446021, 'Death is caused by swallowing small amounts of saliva over a long period of time.', 1003, 0), (446022, 'With actors, all our ages are out there for all to see - you can''t hide anything, really. And it''s kind of a relief. This is my age, this is what I look like without makeup on - who cares? That youth culture - that lying about your age - it''s all denial of death anyway.', 433, 0), (446023, 'I''ve said this over and over, but I''ll say it a million more times - I''m concerned more about the death of a bee than I am about terrorism. Because we''re losing hives and bees by the millions because of such strong pesticides.', 1883, 0), (446024, 'I will admit, like Socrates and Aristotle and Plato and some other philosophers, that there are instances where the death penalty would seem appropriate.', 7905, 0), (446025, 'I won''t forget the hood. I won''t forget the days of catching a bullet on the way to the mailbox or bricks with death threats that somehow made their way through the window.', 71413, 0), (446026, 'There exists in some parts of the world sanctimonious criticism of America''s death penalty, as somehow unworthy of a civilized society.', 21037, 0), (446027, 'At a formal dinner party, the person nearest death should always be seated closest to the bathroom.', 1003, 0), (446028, 'The idea is to die young as late as possible.', 28831, 0), (446029, 'Man always dies before he is fully born.', 190, 0), (446030, 'Fear of death makes us devoid both of valour and religion. For want of valour is want of religious faith.', 32, 0), (446031, 'Liberty for wolves is death to the lambs.', 2828, 0), (446032, 'It is neccessary to have wished for death in order to know how good it is to live.', 319, 0), (446033, 'The appeal of cinema lies in the fear of death.', 216, 0), (446034, 'Death is delightful. Death is dawn, The waking from a weary night Of fevers unto truth and light.', 1247, 0), (446035, 'Life itself is but the shadow of death, and souls departed but the shadows of the living.', 4506, 0), (446036, 'There are certain people that are marked for death. I have my little list of those that treated me unfairly.', 24514, 0), (446037, 'Emigration is no longer a solution; it''s a defeat. People are risking death, drowning every day, but they''re knocking on doors that are not open.', 31617, 0), (446038, 'As the fly bangs against the window attempting freedom while the door stands open, so we bang against death ignoring heaven.', 67402, 0), (446039, 'And I will show that nothing can happen more beautiful than death.', 1127, 0), (446040, 'I''ve always been slightly preoccupied with death or whatever those kind of silly big questions people will tell you to not spend your time worrying about.', 69022, 0), (446041, 'When I first met Alan Parker, who directed ''Angel Heart,'' he''d heard so many horror stories about me that he was literally scared to death of me. Right away, he sat me down and said, ''I''m very scared of you. I''ve heard you''re a very bad boy.''', 70061, 0), (446042, 'Pain is the mind. It''s the thoughts of the mind. Then I get rid of the thoughts, and I get in my witness, which is down in my spiritual heart. The witness that witnesses being. Then those particular thoughts that are painful - love them. I love them to death!', 1853, 0), (446043, 'People think that by living on some mountainside in a tent and being frozen to death by freezing rain, they''re somehow discovering reality, but of course that''s just another fiction dreamed up by a TV producer.', 2312, 0), (446044, 'The silver swan, who, living had no note, When death approached unlocked her silent throat.', 71414, 0), (446045, 'Who is there that can adequately gauge the greatness of the humility, gentleness, self-surrender, revealed by the Lord of majesty in assuming human nature, in accepting the punishment of death, the shame of the cross?', 65719, 0), (446046, 'I joyfully hasten to meet death. If it come before I have had opportunity to develop all my artistic faculties, it will come, my hard fate notwithstanding, too soon, and I should probably wish it later - yet even then I shall be happy, for will it not deliver me from a state of endless suffering?', 1791, 0), (446047, 'In India we only read about death, sickness, terrorism, crime.', 1798, 0), (446048, 'Man and animals are in reality vehicles and conduits of food, tombs of animals, hostels of Death, coverings that consume, deriving life by the death of others.', 1386, 0), (446049, 'It''s not morbid to talk about death. Most people don''t worry about death, they worry about a bad death.', 195, 0), (446050, 'God, who preferred the correction rather than the death of a sinner, did not desire that a homicide be punished by the exaction of another act of homicide.', 69072, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (446051, 'No matter what is happening in life or in the world - war, natural disaster, poor health, pain, the death of loved ones - if existence is filled with art, music and literature, life will be fulfilling, a joy.', 68490, 0), (446052, 'In classical times, it was a capital offense to speculate upon the hour of a king''s death or upon the identity of his successor.', 2074, 0), (446053, 'Many people assume the diseases that kill us are pre-programmed into our genes. High blood pressure by 55, heart attacks at 60, maybe cancer at 70, and so on... But for most of the leading causes of death, our genes usually account for only 10-20 per cent of risk.', 69458, 0), (446054, 'Old age is a tyrant, who forbids, under pain of death, the pleasures of youth.', 154, 0), (446055, 'Some of us can be examples about going ahead and growing, and some of us, unfortunately, don''t make it there, and end up being examples because they had to die. I hit rock bottom, but thank God my bottom wasn''t death.', 71410, 0), (446056, 'Faithfulness to the past can be a kind of death above ground. Writing of the past is a resurrection the past then lives in your words and you are free. ', 3164, 0), (446057, 'I mean, death is a serious thing, certainly not to be sneezed at.', 1259, 0), (446058, 'I want to see the U.S. wiped out. Death to the U.S.', 38353, 0), (446059, 'My old man taught me a lot of stuff in his death that I don''t even know if he would have been able to teach me had he been alive. And that was to never do stuff that can jeopardize the people you love and hurt them.', 71415, 0), (446060, 'Following Michael Brown''s death, I went to Ferguson and met with his parents. I stood with them as they tried to hold their heads high and deal with both their immense loss and the larger issues of police-community relations.', 68935, 0), (446061, 'The first memory I have in the world is of death and tears. That is how I would mark the beginning of my life: the way people mark the end of one. My family had gathered at Papa Joe''s house because Mam'' Grace was slipping away, only I didn''t register it that way. For some reason I thought that it was her birthday.', 7234, 0), (446062, 'Does not the very word ''creative'' mean to build, to initiate, to give out, to act - rather than to be acted upon, to be subjective? Living photography is positive in its approach, it sings a song of life - not death.', 50257, 0), (446063, 'Life is doubt, and faith without doubt is nothing but death.', 1504, 0), (446064, 'Beauty is a precious trace that eternity causes to appear to us and that it takes away from us. A manifestation of eternity, and a sign of death as well.', 2291, 0), (446065, 'Death never takes the wise man by surprise, he is always ready to go.', 2843, 0), (446066, 'For those who live neither with religious consolations about death nor with a sense of death (or of anything else) as natural, death is the obscene mystery, the ultimate affront, the thing that cannot be controlled. It can only be denied.', 4673, 0), (446067, 'The charm of fame is so great that we like every object to which it is attached, even death.', 144, 0), (446068, 'A belief in hell and the knowledge that every ambition is doomed to frustration at the hands of a skeleton have never prevented the majority of human beings from behaving as though death were no more than an unfounded rumor.', 1032, 0), (446069, 'Our law is a Jordanian law that we inherited, which applies to both the West Bank and Gaza, and sets the death penalty for those who sell land to Israelis.', 68676, 0), (446070, 'Fads are the kiss of death. When the fad goes away, you go with it.', 22799, 0), (446071, 'Rock and menopause do not mix. It is not good, it sucks and every day I fight it to the death, or, at the very least, not let it take me over.', 2108, 0), (446072, 'I am not the born how can there be either birth or death for me? ', 4201, 0), (446073, 'Agitate! Agitate! Ought to be the motto of every reformer. Agitation is the opposite of stagnation - the one is life, the other death.', 71416, 0), (446074, 'Saddam''s fate should be in the hands of his country men. They were the major victims of his brutal reign and should decide his life, death, or permanent imprisonment. Personally, I would lock him away forever.', 27500, 0), (446075, 'We were then in a dangerous, helpless situation, exposed daily to perils and death amongst savages and wild beasts, not a white man in the country but ourselves.', 14584, 0), (446076, 'To live without risk for me would be tantamount to death.', 62380, 0), (446077, 'Had it not been for slavery, the death penalty would have likely been abolished in America. Slavery became a haven for the death penalty.', 61929, 0), (446078, 'I am reconciled to my death, but I detest the mode.', 71396, 0), (446079, 'Sleep is lovely, death is better still, not to have been born is of course the miracle.', 1158, 0), (446080, 'I think that we should be eternally vigilant against attempts to check the expression of opinions that we loathe and believe to be fraught with death, unless they so imminently threaten immediate interference with the lawful and pressing purposes of the law that an immediate check is required to save the country.', 24754, 0), (446081, 'The death penalty is being applied in the United States as a fatal lottery.', 68719, 0), (446082, 'To be immortal is commonplace; except for man, all creatures are immortal, for they are ignorant of death; what is divine, terrible, incomprehensible, is to know that one is immortal.', 284, 0), (446083, 'I have thought there was some advantage even in death, by which we mingle with the herd of common men.', 1049, 0), (446084, 'There''s nothing wrong in suffering, if you suffer for a purpose. Our revolution didn''t abolish danger or death. It simply made danger and death worthwhile.', 3173, 0), (446085, 'I have two luxuries to brood over in my walks, your loveliness and the hour of my death. O that I could have possession of them both in the same minute.', 191, 0), (446086, 'For children preserve the fame of a man after his death.', 1882, 0), (446087, 'The writer crafts their ideal world. In my world, everyone has really long conversations or just picks apart pop culture to death and everyone talks in monologue.', 1510, 0), (446088, 'In Seattle, I soon found that my radical ideas and aesthetic explorations - ideas and explorations that in Richmond, Virginia, might have gotten me stoned to death with hush puppies - were not only accepted but occasionally applauded.', 105, 0), (446089, 'Of course, we avoid death. To know something is inevitable is one thing. To accept, to truly feel it... that''s different.', 35830, 0), (446090, 'Libertarians know that a free country has nothing to fear from anyone coming in or going out - while a welfare state is scared to death of poor people coming in and rich people getting out.', 45221, 0), (446091, 'India made a big mistake by signing up to TRIPS. With a population of 1.3 billion, India can''t afford a monopoly in healthcare. Monopolies lead to higher prices and we can''t allow them in a country like India with so much poverty and misery. It was like signing our own death warrant.', 71417, 0), (446092, 'If you look at the beginning of this country, when the pilgrims came to this country, the first year they had a communistic experiment. They said, ''OK, we''re going to take the land, we''re going to work the land together and share in the fruits of our labor.'' They almost starved to death. Almost half of them died that first year.', 67533, 0), (446093, 'A filmmaker doesn''t have to suffer to show suffering. You just have to understand it. You don''t have to die to shoot a death scene.', 18666, 0), (446094, 'Nixon was a bad loser. He hated losing worse than death, and that is why I enjoyed him. We were both football fans, both addicts; and on some days, nothing else mattered.', 126, 0), (446095, 'Even though everybody''s lives are different, in general we''re all human beings, and we go through the same things: disappointments, the pleasures of life, life and death. That''s always been a really big part of the show to me, making sure the audience feels connected, and that carries through to the album.', 68442, 0), (446096, 'I am profoundly fascinated by cruelty, fear, horror and death. My films show my preoccupation with violence, the pathology of violence.', 71418, 0), (446097, 'The obvious objections to the execution of Saddam Hussein are valid and well aired. His death will provoke violent strife between Sunni and Shia Muslims, and between Iraqis in general and the American occupation forces.', 1716, 0), (446098, 'I feel about aging the way William Saroyan said he felt about death: Everybody has to do it, but I always believed an exception would be made in my case.', 29471, 0), (446099, 'For me, since I have a life wish, not a death wish, for me, I was not gambling my life. I was doing something much more beautiful. I was carrying my life across.', 29340, 0), (446100, 'I think if ''The Narrow Road To The Deep North'' is one of the high points of Japanese culture, then the experience of my father, who was a slave laborer on the Death Railway, represents one of its low points.', 9692, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (446101, 'We hear tears loudly on this side of Heaven. What we don''t take time to contemplate are the even louder cheers on the other side of death''s valley.', 1692, 0), (446102, 'The amount of death terror experienced is closely related to the amount of life unlived.', 1196, 0), (446103, 'Prior to penicillin and medical research, death was an everyday occurrence. It was intimate.', 3175, 0), (446104, 'Statistics are the triumph of the quantitative method, and the quantitative method is the victory of sterility and death.', 4439, 0), (446105, 'Everything that gets born dies.', 2128, 0), (446106, 'You''ve never seen death? Look in the mirror every day and you will see it like bees working in a glass hive.', 2343, 0), (446107, 'In order to speak about all and to all, one has to speak of what all know and of the reality common to us all. The sea, rains, necessity, desire, the struggle against death... these are things that unite us all.', 532, 0), (446108, 'Once writing has become your major vice and greatest pleasure, only death can stop it.', 110, 0), (446109, 'If someone were to say that life at hard labor is as painful as death and therefore equally cruel, I should reply that, taking all the unhappy moments of perpetual slavery together, it is perhaps even more painful, but these moments are spread out over a lifetime, and capital punishment exercises all its power in an instant.', 3016, 0), (446110, 'I''m not afraid to die.', 1721, 0), (446111, 'Death is the cure for all diseases.', 4506, 0), (446112, 'I detest life-insurance agents: they always argue that I shall some day die, which is not so.', 9981, 0), (446113, 'I had seen birth and death but had thought they were different.', 1067, 0), (446114, 'Death is a very dull, dreary affair, and my advice to you is to have nothing whatsoever to do with it.', 235, 0), (446115, 'The words of a dead man are modified in the guts of the living.', 219, 0), (446116, 'Some men are alive simply because it is against the law to kill them.', 13154, 0), (446117, 'Love and death are the two great hinges on which all human sympathies turn.', 71419, 0), (446118, 'Birth and death we all move between these two unknowns. ', 24882, 0), (446119, 'Dying is easy, it''s living that scares me to death.', 22705, 0), (446120, 'Grumbling is the death of love.', 5858, 0), (446121, 'The gods conceal from men the happiness of death, that they may endure life.', 62505, 0), (446122, 'A new idea is delicate. It can be killed by a sneer or a yawn it can be stabbed to death by a quip and worried to death by a frown on the right man''s brow. ', 782, 0), (446123, 'Biography lends to death a new terror.', 40, 0), (446124, 'When you break up, your whole identity is shattered. It''s like death.', 70669, 0), (446125, 'On the plus side, death is one of the few things that can be done as easily lying down .', 281, 0), (446126, 'Success is like death. The more successful you become, the higher the houses in the hills get and the higher the fences get.', 60302, 0), (446127, 'Pain and death are part of life. To reject them is to reject life itself.', 62533, 0), (446128, 'The greatest men of a nation are those it puts to death.', 21120, 0), (446129, 'Birth was the death of him.', 1084, 0), (446130, 'Though it be in the power of the weakest arm to take away life, it is not in the strongest to deprive us of death.', 4506, 0), (446131, 'I''m not afraid of death. It''s the stake one puts up in order to play the game of life.', 42142, 0), (446132, 'A useless life is an early death.', 282, 0), (446133, 'The passion of hatred is so long lived and so obstinate a malady that the surest sign of death in a sick person is their desire for reconciliation.', 5879, 0), (446134, 'Your body must become familiar with its death - in all its possible forms and degrees - as a self-evident, imminent, and emotionally neutral step on the way towards the goal you have found worthy of your life.', 851, 0), (446135, 'Death is the veil which those who live call life; They sleep, and it is lifted.', 165, 0), (446136, 'The valiant never taste of death but once.', 13, 0), (446137, 'Men should be bewailed at their birth, and not at their death.', 48659, 0), (446138, 'We are all of us resigned to death: it''s life we aren''t resigned to.', 429, 0), (446139, 'I believe that fear of life brings a greater fear of death.', 67510, 0), (446140, 'When I listen to music, I don''t want to hear about flowers. I like death and destruction.', 55158, 0), (446141, 'I saw also that there was an ocean of darkness and death, but an infinite ocean of light and love, which flowed over the ocean of darkness.', 3771, 0), (446142, 'The death penalty, I think, is a terrible scar on American justice, especially the concept of equal justice under law, but also of due process. And it goes state by state, and it''s different in different states.', 71420, 0), (446143, 'Nothing is more dreadful in life than the profound thought that death may only greet you with eternal nothingness.', 68095, 0), (446144, 'Death is the only pure, beautiful conclusion of a great passion.', 178, 0), (446145, 'I do not care so much for the death of my gunner, as for other passages of my voyage, for I have good friends in England that will bring me off for that.', 71421, 0), (446146, 'Death gives meaning to our lives. It gives importance and value to time. Time would become meaningless if there were too much of it.', 24751, 0), (446147, 'When the courts decide that murderers, rapists, and others who maliciously break our social contract deserve health care that most working Americans can''t afford, they are condemning good people to death.', 67803, 0), (446148, 'The coward sneaks to death the brave live on. ', 71422, 0), (446149, 'I think about death a lot, like I think we all do. I don''t think of suicide as an option, but as fun. It''s an interesting idea that you can control how you go. It''s this thing that''s looming, and you can control it.', 62003, 0), (446150, 'An insatiable appetite for glory leads to sacrifice and death, but innate instinct leads to self-preservation and life.', 2468, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (446151, 'Many cats are the death of the mouse.', 71423, 0), (446152, 'Life comes to the miners out of their deaths, and death out of their lives.', 1505, 0), (446153, 'Death is a very important part of life.', 71424, 0), (446154, 'Nothing in life is certain except death, taxes and the second law of thermodynamics.', 13766, 0), (446155, 'There is nothing glamorous about death.', 67012, 0), (446156, 'Death remains about the one certain fact in the lives of each one of us, and there will be suffering, sorrow, and sadness next week as there was last week.', 9291, 0), (446157, 'Today she is the lady of death, which I believe is the best muse to have.', 44402, 0), (446158, 'All I want is a gentleman. I''m sick to bloody death of bastards.', 60478, 0), (446159, 'I came face to face with death at thirteen years old.', 71300, 0), (446160, 'The American people know that every day 3,000 kids begin to smoke, 1,000 of them die an early death. They''re not going to allow us to go forward this year and not have comprehensive bipartisan legislation. It''s in everybody''s best interest.', 71425, 0), (446161, 'Death is very often referred to as a good career move.', 71426, 0), (446162, 'Dying before dying has two important consequences: It liberates the individual from the fear of death and influences the actual experience of dying at the time of biological demise.', 50366, 0), (446163, 'Oh eyes, no eyes, but fountains fraught with tears; O life, no life, but lively form of death; Oh world, no world, but mass of public wrongs.', 18755, 0), (446164, 'The life of men and women is so cheap and property is so sacred. There are so many of us for one job it matters little if 146 of us are burned to death.', 71427, 0), (446165, 'What are you gonna do, talk the alien to death?', 3628, 0), (446166, 'I was blessed with a birth and a death, and I guess I just want some say in between.', 1251, 0), (446167, 'You haven''t lost anything when you know were it is. Death can hide but not divide.', 1887, 0), (446168, 'Don''t be afraid to feel as angry or as loving as you can, because when you feel nothing, it''s just death.', 20532, 0), (446169, 'Other states are trying to abolish the death penalty... mine''s putting in an express lane.', 1252, 0), (446170, 'I now bid farewell to the country of my birth - of my passions - of my death a country whose misfortunes have invoked my sympathies - whose factions I sought to quell - whose intelligence I prompted to a lofty aim - whose freedom has been my fatal dream. ', 71428, 0), (446171, 'It is a sign of creeping inner death when we can no longer praise the living.', 2567, 0), (446172, 'When death has you by the throat, you don''t mince words.', 9641, 0), (446173, 'To die for one''s country is such a worthy fate that all compete for so beautiful a death.', 3285, 0), (446174, 'To some extent I liken slavery to death.', 1306, 0), (446175, 'Well, there''s a remedy for all things but death, which will be sure to lay us flat one time or other.', 62284, 0), (446176, 'Not even old age knows how to love death.', 139, 0), (446177, 'Each instant of life is a step toward death.', 3285, 0), (446178, 'The miser, starving his brother''s body, starves also his own soul, and at death shall creep out of his great estate of injustice, poor and naked and miserable.', 1771, 0), (446179, 'The slave is doomed to worship time and fate and death, because they are greater than anything he finds in himself, and because all his thoughts are of things which they devour.', 95, 0), (446180, 'Let us eat and drink neither forgetting death unduly nor remembering it. The Lord hath mercy on whom he will have mercy, etc., and the less we think about it the better.', 4111, 0), (446181, 'All stories interest me, and some haunt me until I end up writing them. Certain themes keep coming up: justice, loyalty, violence, death, political and social issues, freedom.', 441, 0), (446182, 'To be clear, climate change is a true 800 pound gorilla in the room. The effects of global warming threaten global environmental upheaval over the coming century. But for South Florida and the Everglades, it could be our death knell if urgent action is not taken.', 70529, 0), (446183, 'Patrick Henry did not say, ''Give me absolutely safety or give me death.'' America is supposed to be about freedom.', 71429, 0), (446184, 'I''m not in favor of the death penalty. But I''m in favor of locking these people away in maximum security units where they can never get out. They can never escape. They can never be paroled. Lock the bad ones away. But you gotta rethink everybody else.', 3490, 0), (446185, 'My mother''s death put me in touch with my most savage self. As I''ve grown up and come to terms with her death and accepted it, the pieces of her that I keep don''t exist materially.', 1199, 0), (446186, 'It''s not the normal way to look at things but I experienced death at a really young age and because of that it''s been part of my mental landscape that death is really very possible.', 66787, 0), (446187, 'Death is the ultimate enemy - and I find nothing reproachable in those who rage mightily against the dying of the light.', 1195, 0), (446188, 'And I love Evander Holyfield to death!', 45107, 0), (446189, 'For me it was a lot harder to come to terms with the death of my grandfather than it was to come to terms with what''s happened to the former Yugoslavia.', 8095, 0), (446190, 'There are some people who walk into a room and they oxygenate it, by their very being there''s fresh air. Then there are those who come in with the smell of death and they suck the life out.', 71430, 0), (446191, 'I''m 64 years old and, yeah, I went through a transition in my life last year, with the death of my son, that woke me up to a lot of things. You know, I''m perfectly happy in my own little groove. Marching along, building my company, and you know, a happy person.', 67908, 0), (446192, 'The good news is that even though we walk through this valley of death, we don''t have to fear, at least not for ourselves! Unfortunately, there is no way to skip over the valley altogether, we must face death and the evidence of evil all around us. But there will come a day... And what a day that will be!', 1986, 0), (446193, 'Death, the real simile for disease - for when we are ill, do we not always feel like we are dying, even if it''s only a little? - remains, despite our secularism, the most metaphoricised phenomenon of all.', 1747, 0), (446194, 'You may have gathered that I am not the most cheerful of revellers - some characterise me as the death and soullessness of any party but it wasn''t always so, believe me.', 1747, 0), (446195, 'Meditation on inevitable death should be performed daily. Every day one should meditate on being carried away by surging waves, falling from thousand-foot cliffs, dying of disease.', 66981, 0), (446196, 'At the end of our lives, we step across the threshold or death and enter into a new and better world. I believe that. It''s just that simple.', 197, 0), (446197, 'If you look in general at people who live in anarchy, they have quite high rates of death from either homicide or warfare or both. Anarchy is one of the main reasons for violence, and it may be the most important.', 3432, 0), (446198, 'What I''m after is not living to 1,000. I''m after letting people avoid death for as long as they want to.', 30464, 0), (446199, 'Am I a trance medium? No. Have I got a gift psychically? Absolutely not. But I believe in the survival of consciousness after death.', 71431, 0), (446200, 'My mother''s death brought me to my knees. She was my hero, my role model, my very best friend. I spoke to her every single day of my life. I really tried hard when I grew up to make her proud of me.', 32356, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (446201, 'I think it''s very dangerous, the idea of celebrity - you have to be constantly controversial to maintain the status of celebrity. Reality TV is the death of entertainment - it''s just mindless TV but popular because of its voyeuristic nature, and people are very voyeuristic.', 70433, 0), (446202, 'Even if we mortgage the next 100 years of generations of human beings, we would not have enough energy to build a Death Star.', 1821, 0), (446203, 'Real heroes are those who face death for a principle - say, to save the lives of others - without any promise of reward.', 17810, 0), (446204, 'I''m interested in time, fame, death, beauty, truth, all those things.', 22775, 0), (446205, 'At the time of his death, John Kennedy had a national security establishment that was a writhing ball of snakes.', 69770, 0), (446206, 'I am more interested in how people interpret the phrase ''Elect The Dead'' than what I may or may not have intended. I named the album after the track, which is a spiritual song about love, life and death and is the heaviest song on the album without having any heavy instruments.', 12800, 0), (446207, 'When you have closed the Bible, you have neither closed God''s mind nor shut God''s mouth. God continues to speak, live and exist. I think we should consult the living God for the living word for living people dealing with death, destruction and despair in the midst of our hurt humanity. I believe love will conquer all.', 3861, 0), (446208, 'Even a cup of coffee tastes so much sweeter because you''ve come once again out of the, literally, out of the edge of death, and that''s the condition I suppose that a lot of artists and writers would like to be in.', 71432, 0), (446209, 'We are eternal beings. We lived as intelligent spirits before this mortal life. We are now living part of eternity. Our mortal birth was not the beginning; death, which faces all of us, is not the end.', 1826, 0), (446210, 'My dad died when I was 23. His death was sudden and shocking - the result of a car crash - and I never got to say goodbye.', 8212, 0), (446211, 'Banks will fee you to death. If you bounce a check, the bank has a policy to re-post the check three more times to see if it will be paid. If it continues to bounce they charge a $30 overdraft every time. So, one bounced check will rack up $90 for the bank.', 70150, 0), (446212, 'I believe in the freedom of choice in both life and death.', 71433, 0), (446213, 'If death weren''t around to ''finalize'' the Darwinian process, we''d all still be amoebas.', 10731, 0), (446214, 'If we heard that somebody starved to death in Sweden or Switzerland, we would be shocked.', 10731, 0), (446215, 'I blame feminism and Facebook for the death of the American automobile. I''m a Republican, so I blame everything on feminism - or commies.', 10731, 0), (446216, 'Of all the logical impasses, unknowings, paradoxes, and terrors that provoke laughter, death by its finality and unsolvable mystery is paramount.', 71434, 0), (446217, 'I was born on January 8, 1942, exactly three hundred years after the death of Galileo. I estimate, however, that about two hundred thousand other babies were also born that day. I don''t know whether any of them was later interested in astronomy.', 1222, 0), (446218, 'I have my very own Oscar now to be with me until death us do part.', 18244, 0), (446219, 'The Secret Revelation of John opens, again, in crisis. The disciple John, grieving Jesus'' death, is walking toward the temple when he meets a Pharisee who mocks him for having been deceived by a false messiah. These taunts echoed John''s own fear and doubt.', 10783, 0), (446220, 'Cinema sustains life. It captures death in its progress.', 13566, 0), (446221, 'My death is incidental, and I worry very much about my loved ones and, you know, would like to make it as easy as possible for them. Or wish I could will away whatever, you know, the sadness they will feel when I die. But for me, nothing. The world goes on.', 10605, 0), (446222, 'I never had a conscious fear of death, but I did have a conscious fear of sickness. By the time I completed medical school, that fear was gone.', 13644, 0), (446223, 'Obviously, there''s a part of me that takes the world of violence and death very seriously. However, when it comes to protection, or when it comes to just the skill of shooting... I''ve gone to the range with sniper rifles and things like that.', 1380, 0), (446224, 'With plastic surgery, the general anesthetic is like a black-velvety sleep, and that''s what death is - without waking up to someone clapping and going, ''Joan, wake up, it''s all over and you''re looking pretty''.', 17330, 0), (446225, '''Sesame Street''s'' genius lies in finding gentle ways to talk about hard things - death, divorce, danger - in terms that children understand and accept.', 36805, 0), (446226, 'The leading cause of death for girls 15 to 19 worldwide is not accident or violence or disease; it is complications from pregnancy. Girls under 15 are up to five times as likely to die while having children than are women in their 20s, and their babies are more likely to die as well.', 36805, 0), (446227, 'Drake''s my little brother; I love him to death, and he''s family-oriented.', 67823, 0), (446228, 'When I first came into parliament, there was, on average, a by-election every three months - due not to MPs bailing out, but because of the death rate.', 67458, 0), (446229, 'I''m a huge animal lover - I love animals to death. I''ve got tortoises and three dogs, and I''ve had a million animals in the past. I just think that we should do all we can to take care of them.', 71435, 0), (446230, 'At the heart of Christian faith is the story of Jesus'' death and resurrection.', 4328, 0), (446231, 'We''ve enshrined the purity, sanctity, value, and importance of bringing children into the world, yet we don''t discuss death. There used to be an enshrined period where mourning was a necessary part of going through the process of grieving; death wasn''t considered morbid or antisocial. But that''s totally gone.', 66787, 0), (446232, 'I''ve done a lot of death cartoons - tombstones, Grim Reaper, illness, obituaries... I''m not great at analyzing things, but my guess is that maybe the only relief from the terror of being alive is jokes.', 8062, 0), (446233, 'I love my wife to death. I mean my ex-wife.', 71436, 0), (446234, 'No city owns me, you know what I''m saying? I''m from New York, but no city owns me. Nobody can bottle up my sound and box me in. Yes, I am a rapper, but am I a New York rapper? No. I am from New York, I love New York to death, but I will not conform myself to one place, no.', 71437, 0), (446235, 'Good taste is death vulgarity is life. ', 57412, 0), (446236, 'If you''re going to write about war, the ugly side is inevitable. Suffering and death are obviously part of war.', 30972, 0), (446237, 'I say that no man can be greater than the man who bravely and heroically sacrifices his life for the good of others. No man can be greater than the one who meets death face to face, and yet will not shrink from what he believes to be his highest duty.', 67335, 0), (446238, 'If we ignore our death, we end up just going around completely oblivious to why we do the things we do!', 7801, 0), (446239, 'For thousands of years, we did have death surrounding us, and we did have people die in the home. You would take care of your own end. You would do ritual processes, and you would be involved in it, and that''s been taken away in the Western world.', 7801, 0), (446240, 'Humans are insane. We kill our own people, starve our own people, sell them, work them to death, beat them, don''t give them affordable/free/good healthcare, and let them live in misery, while a few of us have - we have all we want. We are evil.', 35843, 0), (446241, 'I have been connected with the Niels Bohr Institute since the completion of my university studies, first as a research fellow and, from 1956, as a professor of physics at the University of Copenhagen. After the death of my father in 1962, I followed him as director of the Institute until 1970.', 71438, 0), (446242, 'You''re trying to write about something that''s sacred. You''re trying to bring the seriousness of life and death to it, and you''re trying to find a way to dramatize it, and you''re trying to give language to it, which is inadequate. But it''s important to try.', 19836, 0), (446243, 'In an area of more than 1,000 war graves and with birdsong as the only sound, I contemplated the thin margin between life and death. If the sniper''s bullet had been just two feet to one side, my father''s life would have been over, aged just 27, and I would never have been born.', 71439, 0), (446244, '''Hard Hit,'' a YA collection of poems, explores the country of grief and survival. Mark, a 16-year-old boy and skilled pitcher, must confront the coming death of his beloved father with the help of his friends, family, baseball, and an idiosyncratic belief in God. I used my own experience of my parents'' deaths to inform this journey.', 71440, 0), (446245, 'The minute we stop learning, we begin death, the process of dying. We learn from each other with every action we perform. We are teaching goodness or evil every time we step out of the house and into the street.', 406, 0), (446246, 'Infectious diseases have become less prominent as causes of death and disability in regions of improved sanitation and adequate supplies of antibiotics.', 63538, 0), (446247, 'After my death, the molecules of my being will return to the earth and the sky. They came from the stars. I am of the stars.', 37323, 0), (446248, 'I''ve stopped reading about the death of books because it''s wasteful and morbid and insulting to the authors, agents, publishers, booksellers, critics, and readers that keep the world community of fiction interesting.', 13083, 0), (446249, 'The typical Western diet is the number-one cause of premature death and the number-one cause of disability. In other words, a long and healthy life is largely a matter of choice.', 69458, 0), (446250, 'Always read something that will make you look good if you die in the middle of it.', 10731, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (446251, 'Know one knows whether death, which people fear to be the greatest evil, may not be the greatest good.', 51, 0), (446252, 'An unused life is an early death.', 282, 0), (446253, 'Death most resembles a prophet who is without honor in his own land or a poet who is a stranger among his people.', 5542, 0), (446254, 'Prepare for death, if here at night you roam, and sign your will before you sup from home.', 2087, 0), (446255, 'Whether you like it or not, you''re forced to come to the realisation that death is out there. But I don''t fear death, I''m a fatalist. I believe when it''s your time, that''s it. It''s the hand you''re dealt.', 2269, 0), (446256, 'We as Americans believe it''s OK to kill people. We believe it''s OK to invade a country that had nothing to do with 9/11. We think it''s OK to invade a country where we think Osama Bin Laden is and he''s in the other country. So we just go in and we just kill. And we have the death penalty we sanction it. ', 17499, 0), (446257, 'If nothing else, there''s comfort in recognising that no matter how much we fail and sin, death will limit our suffering.', 30, 0), (446258, 'There''s something about death that is comforting. The thought that you could die tomorrow frees you to appreciate your life now.', 1380, 0), (446259, 'In cold weather states like Vermont, where the weather can get to 20 below zero, home heating assistance is critically important. In fact, it is a life and death issue.', 40174, 0), (446260, '''Biutiful'' is not about death. It''s about life. It''s a hymn to life.', 60783, 0), (446261, 'Death is frightening, and so is Eternal Life.', 12469, 0), (446262, 'I was not encouraged to follow the career of a writer because my parents thought that I was going to starve to death. They thought nobody can make a living from being a writer in Brazil. They were not wrong.', 34, 0), (446263, 'The more you live in the present moment, the more the fear of death disappears.', 378, 0), (446264, 'To himself everyone is immortal; he may know that he is going to die, but he can never know that he is dead.', 4111, 0), (446265, 'I hate death it takes people away from you. You''re left feeling rudderless. ', 14227, 0), (446266, 'This country is being managed to death, being public related to death.', 13666, 0), (446267, 'I don''t think I would want the responsibility for enforcing the death penalties. There''s always the inevitable question of whether someone you gave the order to execute might truly have been innocent.', 16709, 0), (446268, 'Previous generations understood about death, and undoubtedly would have seen a reasonable amount of death. Once you get into the Victorian era, you might well have seen the funerals of many of your siblings before you were very old.', 195, 0), (446269, 'Nothing can happen more beautiful than death.', 1127, 0), (446270, 'I''m not afraid of death, but I resent it. I think it''s unfair and irritating.', 2042, 0), (446271, '''Tis very certain the desire of life prolongs it.', 62558, 0), (446272, 'In shuttering Yucca Mountain, Obama makes it extremely likely that nuclear power in the United States will continue its long, slow, and extremely welcome death.', 70991, 0), (446273, 'When death, the great reconciler, has come, it is never our tenderness that we repent of, but our severity.', 215, 0), (446274, 'When death comes it is never our tenderness that we repent from, but our severity.', 215, 0), (446275, 'In every parting there is an image of death.', 215, 0), (446276, 'Thanks to presidential immunity and executive control of the Justice Department, there are no consequences to executive branch lawbreaking. And when it comes to presidential lawbreaking, the sitting president could literally strangle someone to death on national television and meet with no consequences.', 17797, 0), (446277, 'No one else can take risks for us, or face our losses on our behalf, or give us self-esteem. No one