INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (446351, 'Even one heatstroke death is one too many because every death caused by leaving a child unattended in a hot car is 100 percent avoidable.', 68215, 0), (446352, 'If you don''t have any fight in you, you might as well be dead.', 69376, 0), (446353, 'I think, in real life, when we''re facing death - that is, when we come out on the other side of it, whether it''s death of a friend or a family member - you come out on the other side of the mourning cherishing your life that much more.', 26266, 0), (446354, 'I hope to die in the saddle seat.', 22518, 0), (446355, 'Those who welcome death have only tried it from the ears up.', 63304, 0), (446356, 'But for me, it is when a student has died. I find the death of a young person the most difficult and painful of times. To explain it to other young people, to see a bright future snuffed out, is just awful. I am haunted by those deaths.', 71065, 0), (446357, 'I shall not die of a cold. I shall die of having lived.', 307, 0), (446358, 'I was court-martialled in my absence, and sentenced to death in my absence, so I said they could shoot me in my absence.', 9701, 0), (446359, 'Once a disease has entered the body, all parts which are healthy must fight it: not one alone, but all. Because a disease might mean their common death. Nature knows this; and Nature attacks the disease with whatever help she can muster.', 2652, 0), (446360, 'When you''re dead, you''re dead. That''s it.', 5858, 0), (446361, 'Dickinson is my hero because she was a joker, because she would never explain, because as a poet she confronted pain, dread and death, and because she was capable of speaking of those matters with both levity and seriousness. She''s my hero because she was a metaphysical adventurer.', 9941, 0), (446362, 'I was in a rock band; I was my own folk singer; I was in a death metal band for a very short time; I was in a cover band, a jazz band, a blues band. I was in a gospel choir.', 71444, 0), (446363, 'For tis not in mere death that men die most.', 157, 0), (446364, 'The Greeks said grandly in their tragic phrase, ''Let no one be called happy till his death;'' to which I would add, ''Let no one, till his death, be called unhappy.''', 157, 0), (446365, 'I like death. I''m a big fan of it.', 14948, 0), (446366, 'The death of what''s dead is the birth of what''s living.', 68391, 0), (446367, 'Only comedians can talk about death, life, God and Virgin Mary. If I was a tragic actor, I couldn''t allow myself. But with this accent I can do it. I can talk with death in person because I am a clown. Yes. And I am proud to be a clown - very much.', 69160, 0), (446368, 'We were aware of the fact that death walks hand in hand with struggle.', 40220, 0), (446369, 'I spend a lot of time with Buddhists. I''m not a Buddhist, but their relationship with death interests me.', 7820, 0), (446370, 'Cardiovascular diseases are the leading cause of death in women.', 71445, 0), (446371, 'Man dies of cold, not of darkness.', 1504, 0), (446372, 'With attention deficit democracy, I am trying to wake up people to how the combination of mass ignorance, fear mongering by the government, and lying politicians is putting our entire system of government to a death spiral.', 16688, 0), (446373, 'We ourselves can die with comfort and even with joy if we know that death is but a passport to blessedness, that this intellect, freed from all material chains, shall rise and shine.', 71446, 0), (446374, 'He who is completely sanctified, or cleansed from all sin, and dies in this state, is fit for glory.', 49232, 0), (446375, 'I can''t have white roses. They symbolize death.', 71447, 0), (446376, 'I chose not to put a wig on. The reason why I chose to come out with the cancer thing is because there''s somebody out there who can see that all sickness isn''t unto death. That it''s something you can''t change at that point in time, so you just got to go with it. Don''t be ashamed. Don''t be ashamed of looking at yourself.', 71448, 0), (446377, 'I got well by talking. Death could not get a word in edgewise, grew discouraged, and traveled on.', 43, 0), (446378, 'You know, your first album is about really amazing things. Your first album is always about coming of age, first love, first loss, usually you suffer a first loss of someone that you love to death, even, you know, really big life lessons, things you learn from your parents'' divorce or from the travels that you took.', 71449, 0), (446379, 'None of us, in our culture of comfort, know how to prepare ourselves for dying, but that''s what we should do every day. Every single day, we die a thousand deaths.', 199, 0), (446380, 'If you die in an elevator, be sure to push the Up button.', 1260, 0), (446381, 'Some people are so afraid to die that they never begin to live.', 672, 0), (446382, 'The death industry markets caskets and embalming under the rubric of helping bodies look ''natural,'' but our current death customs are as natural as training majestic creatures like bears and elephants to dance in cute little outfits, or erecting replicas of the Eiffel Tower and Venetian canals in the middle of the harsh American desert.', 7801, 0), (446383, 'Death is better than slavery.', 70830, 0), (446384, 'The poet does not fear death, not because he believes in the fantasy of heroes, but because death constantly visits his thoughts and is thus an image of a serene dialogue.', 55576, 0), (446385, 'We''re also the only country that has the Death Penalty. That''s something to boast about, isn''t it?', 71450, 0), (446386, 'Johnny Ringo to me was just the best antagonist that I''ve ever played, because I played him as a guy who has a death wish and had done everything that he wanted in life. As far as he was concerned, a gun fight was about as exciting as it was going to get.', 67199, 0), (446387, 'There must be a punitive expedition against the Jews in Russia, a punitive expedition which will expect: death sentence and execution. Then the world will see the end of the Jews is also the end of Bolshevism.', 71451, 0), (446388, 'To date or not to date that is the question. It''s almost as important as Shakespeare''s to be or not to be which deals with death.', 70752, 0), (446389, 'Art has two constant, two unending concerns: It always meditates on death and thus always creates life. All great, genuine art resembles and continues the Revelation of St John.', 925, 0), (446390, 'Death is not more certainly a separation of our souls from our bodies than the Christian life is a separation of our souls from worldly tempers, vain indulgences, and unnecessary cares.', 21439, 0), (446391, 'But the issue is not only life and death but our existence before God and our being judged by him. All of us were sinners before him and worthy of condemnation.', 1758, 0), (446392, 'Death is the beginning of something.', 51113, 0), (446393, 'Sometimes the early bird gets the worm, but sometimes the early bird gets frozen to death.', 71452, 0), (446394, 'The Death of Advertising? I think that''s in the book of Revelation. It''s the day when people everywhere become satisfied with their weight, their hair, their skin, their wardrobe, and their aroma.', 67366, 0), (446395, 'When we have done our best, we can, as a united people, take whatever may befall with calm courage and confidence that this old nation will survive and if death should come to many of us, death is not the end.', 67600, 0), (446396, 'Hell, madam, is to love no longer.', 4300, 0), (446397, 'All our knowledge merely helps us to die a more painful death than animals that know nothing.', 2006, 0), (446398, 'If you make every game a life and death proposition, you''re going to have problems. For one thing, you''ll be dead a lot.', 7825, 0), (446399, 'Father''s Day was great, but all the family gatherings brought up my mother''s death. Maybe it''s me, because I am a wimp. We would get together, but there was someone missing!', 71453, 0), (446400, 'We cannot banish dangers, but we can banish fears. We must not demean life by standing in awe of death.', 32896, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (446401, 'A detective sees death in all the various forms at least five times a week.', 71454, 0), (446402, 'I have been here before as a spirit - this is just my physical body, it is just an overcoat. And at death, you will take the overcoat off.', 71455, 0), (446403, 'Becoming a parent gives you access to a whole world of feeling. It gives you a much stronger sense of life and death: becoming a father made me realise my own mortality.', 69984, 0), (446404, 'I almost always start with setting! I have to know the world before I know how to populate it. I have a tendency to play with doors - between life and death, human and monster, mundane and magic - and with ''ADSOM,'' I knew I wanted to play with the physical doors between worlds.', 1470, 0), (446405, 'His death was the first time that Ed Wynn ever made anyone sad.', 62651, 0), (446406, 'I don''t believe in death.', 71456, 0), (446407, 'Lovers of air travel find it exhilarating to hang poised between the illusion of immortality and the fact of death.', 58721, 0), (446408, 'Death by starvation is slow.', 71457, 0), (446409, 'Call no man happy before he dies, he is at best but fortunate.', 2635, 0), (446410, 'Death''s in the good-bye.', 164, 0), (446411, 'Death borders upon our birth, and our cradle stands in the grave.', 64945, 0), (446412, 'Death is the tyrant of the imagination.', 69102, 0), (446413, 'Is there a point at which we hit a tipping point and all of this economic, cultural and moral trouble sends us into a death spiral we can''t get out of?', 17590, 0), (446414, 'She goes through the vale of death alone, each time a babe is born. As it is the right neither of man nor the state to coerce her into this ordeal, so it is her right to decide whether she will endure it.', 18058, 0), (446415, 'I am not a ''defender'' of the September 11 attacks, but simply pointing out that if U.S. foreign policy results in massive death and destruction abroad, we cannot feign innocence when some of that destruction is returned.', 16717, 0), (446416, 'From birth to death, anyone can fish. I just think it''s fantastic to see old people going fishing with young people and teaching them things. I''m very, very critical.', 71458, 0), (446417, 'The timing of death, like the ending of a story, gives a changed meaning to what preceded it.', 42405, 0), (446418, 'Birth and death are the most singular events we experience - and the contemplation of death, as of birth, should be a thing of beauty, not ignobility.', 63958, 0), (446419, 'Soldiers are citizens of death''s grey land, drawing no dividend from time''s tomorrows.', 8904, 0), (446420, 'If fame is to come only after death, I am in no hurry for it.', 71459, 0), (446421, 'If you don''t have imagination, you stop being human; animals don''t have imagination; Alzheimer''s is the death of imagination.', 12351, 0), (446422, 'Well the themes for me were and remain sex and love and grief and death - the things that make us and undo us, create and destroy, how we breed and disappear and the emotional context that surrounds these events.', 36219, 0), (446423, 'Fling but a stone, the giant dies.', 29601, 0), (446424, 'You don''t send a man to his death because you want a hero.', 42558, 0), (446425, 'The prime minister found something hopeful in the man''s eyes and manner. The 30 or so people who run this world analyze one another that way and then make decisions of life and death for us. Scary, but true.', 64069, 0), (446426, 'I guess I don''t believe that death is the end.', 68646, 0), (446427, 'It was from an old friend who thought he was dying. Anyway, he said, ''Life and death issues don''t come along that often, thank God, so don''t treat everything like it''s life or death. Go easier.''', 54019, 0), (446428, 'How many wives have been forced by the death of well-intentioned but too protective husbands to face reality late in life, bewildered and frightened because they were strangers to it!', 71460, 0), (446429, 'Death calls ye to the crowd of common men.', 59138, 0), (446430, 'I can''t let my mother''s death have been in vain. Democracy is the best revenge, and we will have it.', 71461, 0), (446431, 'You think, eventually, that nothing can disturb you and that your nerves are impregnable. Yet, looking down at that familiar face, I realized that death is something to which we never become calloused.', 71462, 0), (446432, 'I am not afraid of death, but would not want to die in some obscure or pointless way.', 1921, 0), (446433, 'Nothing that is really good and God-like dies.', 71463, 0), (446434, 'It is only in the light of the inescapable fact of death that a person can adequately engage and enter upon the mysterious fact of life.', 71464, 0), (446435, 'He who doesn''t fear death dies only once.', 71465, 0), (446436, 'Death is the last enemy: once we''ve got past that I think everything will be alright.', 54873, 0), (446437, 'I have a dream that my four little children will one day live in a nation where they will not be judged by the color of their skin, but by the content of their character.', 21767, 0), (446438, 'Racism is still with us. But it is up to us to prepare our children for what they have to meet, and, hopefully, we shall overcome.', 19482, 0), (446439, 'Here are the values that I stand for: honesty, equality, kindness, compassion, treating people the way you want to be treated and helping those in need. To me, those are traditional values.', 1217, 0), (446440, 'If we cannot now end our differences, at least we can help make the world safe for diversity.', 1680, 0), (446441, 'The worst form of inequality is to try to make unequal things equal.', 1116, 0), (446442, 'I speak not for myself but for those without voice... those who have fought for their rights... their right to live in peace, their right to be treated with dignity, their right to equality of opportunity, their right to be educated.', 1851, 0), (446443, 'No struggle can ever succeed without women participating side by side with men.', 1480, 0), (446444, 'The earth is the mother of all people, and all people should have equal rights upon it.', 4664, 0), (446445, 'If you want to see the true measure of a man, watch how he treats his inferiors, not his equals.', 28, 0), (446446, 'True equality means holding everyone accountable in the same way, regardless of race, gender, faith, ethnicity - or political ideology.', 68666, 0), (446447, 'Education promotes equality and lifts people out of poverty. It teaches children how to become good citizens. Education is not just for a privileged few, it is for everyone. It is a fundamental human right.', 21719, 0), (446448, 'There should be no discrimination against languages people speak, skin color, or religion.', 1851, 0), (446449, 'Racism oppresses its victims, but also binds the oppressors, who sear their consciences with more and more lies until they become prisoners of those lies. They cannot face the truth of human equality because it reveals the horror of the injustices they commit.', 71466, 0), (446450, 'Rightful liberty is unobstructed action according to our will within limits drawn around us by the equal rights of others. I do not add ''within the limits of the law'' because law is often but the tyrant''s will, and always so when it violates the rights of the individual.', 1207, 0);
