 us will be extremely challenging as the Tory party continue with their austerity agenda and as we continue to resolve the issues of the past and build unity, reconciliation, and equality.', 67683, 0), (446679, 'My feeling is, having lived in different classes, that people want equality of opportunity... that''s the thing that makes me despair: the idea that people aren''t given equality of opportunity.', 825, 0), (446680, 'The storm and stress period of women and the new social and psychological formations thereby entailed must indeed extend far into the twentieth century. This period of conflict will cease only when woman within and out of marriage shall have received legal equality with man.', 62381, 0), (446681, 'Dr. King challenged our country to fulfill the promises of liberty, equality, and justice prescribed in the founding of our great nation. Leading by example, he stressed the teachings of tolerance, service, and love, regardless of race, color, or creed.', 67049, 0), (446682, 'Propelled by freedom of faith, gender equality and economic justice for all, India will become a modern nation. Minor blemishes cannot cloak the fact that India is becoming such a modern nation: no faith is in danger in our country, and the continuing commitment to gender equality is one of the great narratives of our times.', 71498, 0), (446683, 'Imperfect though it may be, the Beijing Platform for Action is the strongest statement of consensus on women''s equality, empowerment and justice ever produced by governments.', 18087, 0), (446684, 'Gender equality cannot be achieved by cutting programs that allow girls to get the same chance to compete, learn, and play. The United States has had a solid history of commitment to its female athletes and expanding opportunity for women, and it is imperative that we continue on this path.', 71499, 0), (446685, 'I hope that by just being a competent member and expressing informed views on issues that aren''t related to issues of LGBT equality, Republicans see me as a general asset.', 71500, 0), (446686, 'In Canada, women''s rights are a vital part of our effort to build a society of real equality - not just for some, but for all Canadians. A society in which women no longer encounter discrimination nor are shut out from opportunities open to others.', 71481, 0), (446687, 'What is being called the UN ''gender architecture'' is more like a shack. Women need a bigger global house if equality is ever to become a reality.', 64005, 0), (446688, 'Among the best traitors Ireland has ever had, Mother Church ranks at the very top, a massive obstacle in the path to equality and freedom. She has been a force for conservatism... to ward off threats to her own security and influence.', 63078, 0), (446689, 'Mr. Christ, I read you as an infinitely patient entity who, as they say, often works in mysterious ways, a rebel unafraid to take the tougher, less traveled paths. Seems to me you''re playing the long game. Is that why more states are coming out in favor of marriage equality? Is that why the Affordable Care Act is now with us?', 68, 0), (446690, 'With patient and firm determination, I am going to press on for jobs. I''m going to press on for equality. I''m going to press on for the sake of our children. I''m going to press on for the sake of all those families who are struggling right now. I don''t have time to feel sorry for myself. I don''t have time to complain. I am going to press on.', 1693, 0), (446691, 'The way the Democrats go about seeking equality is to lower people at the top.', 17531, 0), (446692, 'It is better that some should be unhappy rather than that none should be happy, which would be the case in a general state of equality.', 2087, 0), (446693, 'Subordination tends greatly to human happiness. Were we all upon an equality, we should have no other enjoyment than mere animal pleasure.', 2087, 0), (446694, 'If you believe in equality, if you believe in standing up for the rights of all, especially for people most affected by bigotry and discrimination, then you have no choice but to be present and accounted for when it comes to standing up for gays and lesbians in our society.', 17499, 0), (446695, 'In terms of my involvement in ''don''t ask, don''t tell'' and marriage equality and anti-bullying and social emotional learning in schools - these are all things that arise out of my relationship with the world and with my fans.', 47, 0), (446696, 'I believe in the spirit of equality and the spirit of this country as one of love and compassion and kindness.', 47, 0), (446697, 'As equality increases, so does the number of people struggling for predominance.', 12469, 0), (446698, 'True gender equality in Scotland - and elsewhere - is still some way off.', 71489, 0), (446699, 'My pledge to you is that the SNP will put women and gender equality right at the heart of the Westminster agenda.', 71489, 0), (446700, 'Nelson Mandela is physically separated from us, but his soul and spirit will never die. He belongs to the whole world because he is an icon of equality, freedom and love, the values we need all the time everywhere.', 1851, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (446701, 'The perfection of our union, especially our commitment to equality of opportunity, has been a story of constant striving to live up to our Founding principles. This is what Abraham Lincoln meant when he said, ''In giving freedom to the slave, we assure freedom to the free - honorable alike in what we give, and what we preserve.''', 66572, 0), (446702, 'As slavery died for the greater good of America, and the movement for equality sputtered to life, the white woman was on the cover of every American magazine. She was the dazzling jewel on every movie screen, the glory of every commercial and television show.', 70444, 0), (446703, 'Each country has a soul, and France''s soul is equality.', 67005, 0), (446704, 'Conservatives often say that we should care not about equality of outcomes but about equality of opportunity.', 70991, 0), (446705, 'Republican presidents talk about freedom. Democratic presidents talk about equality.', 70991, 0), (446706, 'Most Americans are fiscally conservative and socially liberal. I''m advocating a balanced budget. But along with that, look, there should be gay marriage equality. A woman should have the right to choose. Let''s not build a fence across the border.', 68241, 0), (446707, 'It''s about our ability precisely to integrate a people and offer jobs, and that, for me, is one of the key rationales of the reforms I''m pushing, and I''m a strong believer in that when you lift barriers, when you deregulate a lot of stuff, basically you improve the equality of opportunities.', 68911, 0), (446708, 'It''s a facet of the gay rights movement that people don''t think about enough. Why suddenly marriage equality? Because it wasn''t until 1981 that the court struck down Louisiana''s ''head and master rule,'' that the husband was head and master of the house.', 28287, 0), (446709, 'I''m doing ''Rock of Ages'' one day, making out with Russell Brand. Soon after that, I''m advocating