ces are important.', 1851, 0), (447016, 'Adolescence is just one big walking pimple.', 51091, 0), (447017, 'As a teenager I was so insecure. I was the type of guy that never fitted in because he never dared to choose. I was convinced I had absolutely no talent at all. For nothing. And that thought took away all my ambition too.', 148, 0), (447018, 'I don''t believe in ''thinking'' old. Although I''ve transitioned through many bodies - a baby, toddler, child, teen, young adult, mid-life and older adult - my spirit is unchanged. I support my body with exercise, my mind with reading and writing, and my spirit with the knowing that I am part of the Divine source of all life.', 21729, 0), (447019, 'So many people try to grow up too fast, and it''s not fun! You should stay a kid as long as possible!', 67817, 0), (447020, 'For me, the teen years were all about searching for a place for myself, wondering why I seemed so different than everyone else, wondering especially why no one could look past the surface and figure out who I really was underneath.', 3748, 0), (447021, 'Friendships in childhood are usually a matter of chance, whereas in adolescence they are most often a matter of choice.', 71568, 0), (447022, 'The toddler must say no in order to find out who she is. The adolescent says no to assert who she is not.', 71567, 0), (447023, 'Adolescents are not monsters. They are just people trying to learn how to make it among the adults in the world, who are probably not so sure themselves.', 813, 0), (447024, 'I have this sense that I didn''t really start growing up until my twenties.', 70658, 0), (447025, 'You''ve got to grow up sometime.', 70658, 0), (447026, 'I was considered chubby as a teen.', 67012, 0), (447027, 'Being a teenager is an amazing time and a hard time. It''s when you make your best friends - I have girls who will never leave my heart and I still talk to. You get the best and the worst as a teen. You have the best friendships and the worst heartbreaks.', 