ve. That being said, it''s very demanding of you, in so many different ways.', 70139, 0), (447062, 'Growing up, I wanted desperately to please, to be a good girl.', 70251, 0), (447063, 'I was a teen idol and that has a short shelf life.', 71575, 0), (447064, 'To an adolescent, there is nothing in the world more embarrassing than a parent.', 2223, 0), (447065, 'If you just watch a teenager, you see a lot of uncertainty.', 47322, 0), (447066, 'Time scoots along pretty fast when you grow up.', 70613, 0), (447067, 'In the public, it seems to be painted that when minorities get pregnant, they need to get abortions, especially when it comes to teen pregnancy. It''s like, when black girls are pregnant, it''s like a statistic, but when white girls get pregnant, they get a TV show.', 67856, 0), (447068, 'My whole life, growing up, I always wanted to be in comedy. I never felt comfortable doing the ''teen hunk'' thing.', 69217, 0), (447069, 'The endless teen franchises that come out of Hollywood... more often than not, the central character doesn''t have any discernible character traits. They''re just the young, good-looking guy who goes on this journey. They''re always played by fantastic young actors, but ultimately, they''re not very interesting characters.', 68281, 0), (447070, 'Your modern teenager is not about to listen to advice from an old person, defined as a person who remembers when there was no Velcro.', 2223, 0), (447071, 'To all those mothers and fathers who are struggling with teen-agers, I say, just be patient: even though it looks like you can''t do anything right for a number of years, parents become popular again when kids reach 20.', 7224, 0), (447072, 'When I look in the mirror I see the girl I was when I was growing up, with braces, crooked teeth, a baby face and a skinny body.', 71576, 0), (447073, 'No matter how good you are, at some point your kids are gonna have to create their own independence and think that Mom and Dad aren''t cool, just to establish themselves. That''s what adolescence is about. They''re gonna go through that no matter what.', 18483, 0), (447074, 'Female adolescence is - universally - an emotionally and psychologically intense period.', 28451, 0), (447075, 'I love the live performances and Las Vegas. I also like making films that are being discovered by another generation. Having been a teen idol of the ''60s is great because you realize you left your generation with a smile and good memories.', 69095, 0), (447076, 'We won a contest at the teen fair in Vancouver and the first prize was a recording contract and we recorded at a radio station on the stairway, and we did a record and it got put out.', 71577, 0), (447077, 'Teen pop will never die as long as there are teens and popular music. It just takes a different head.', 58477, 0), (447078, 'When I was a teenager I would lock myself in the bathroom for hours, bouffanting my hair like Patty Duke and trying to recreate Barbra Streisand''s flawless eyeliner, only to comb it all out and wash it all off before stepping out into the world a butchish bisexual teen.', 28432, 0), (447079, 'I like having young assistants in my office; they have energy, and I spend time with them to make sure they understand what we''re doing. By investing in them, I''m investing in the magazine. All over ''Vogue,'' ''Teen Vogue,'' and ''Men''s Vogue,'' there are people who have been through not only my office but also many other offices at ''Vogue.''', 1360, 0), (447080, 'During my teen years, I was real emotional. I could be really up or down.', 67003, 0), (447081, 'I won Miss Teen World, and then a movie rep saw me on the pageant website and thought that I had the perfect image for the role in ''Madrasapattinam.''', 69348, 0), (447082, 'That can be the most painstaking aspect of being a teen, figuring out what the world really looks like. If you find someone in a book, you know you''re not alone and that''s what''s so comforting about books.', 1421, 0), (447083, 'As a teen, I heard the second Velvet Underground album, ''White Light/White Heat,'' and it was too much for my limited scope of appreciation. It was intense, but I didn''t get it.', 68, 0), (447084, 'I''m a comic nerd. I''m a former serious collector for much of my childhood and early teen years I wanted to draw underground comics.', 6719, 0), (447085, 'Can you imagine peaking as a teen? I think if you peak in high school, there''s a problem. That''s what my sister always said: ''Don''t worry, you''ll peak later.''', 2202, 0), (447086, 'I was one of those daughters who saw my mother as my enemy when I was a teen.', 41330, 0), (447087, 'At the time I came along, Hollywood''s idea of teen movies meant there had to be a lot of nudity, usually involving boys in pursuit of sex, and pretty gross overall. Either that or a horror movie. And the last thing Hollywood wanted in their teen movies was teenagers!', 55317, 0), (447088, 'Honestly, I never thought I''d actually be playing a teen lesbian. I didn''t think it was going to go this far. But I''m glad that it did, because there have been a lot of fans who have expressed that they''ve been going through similar situations in their lives.', 4603, 0), (447089, 'Even when I was a teen model, I didn''t think it was fair that I had to enter the acting world to get insurance.', 1725, 0), (447090, 'I would not recommend a teen getting into modeling if they''re not solid when it comes to their grades and school. That comes first. My mother always told me that came first.', 1725, 0), (447091, 'I''ve started ordering out of teen catalogues! T-shirts, little coats, and jackets for around $35 - they''re amazing. I''ve become a really big fan of Urban Outfitters, Alloy and Anthropologie. Because I''ll pay for quality, but I will not just pay for trend. Psychologically, I have trouble with that.', 26172, 0), (447092, 'I remember the first time I saw the ''Smells Like Teen Spirit'' video. I will never forget that day. I just wanted to see Kurt Cobain''s face. I had a feeling he was very cute. But, I couldn''t see his face. When I finally did see him, he was even cuter than I imagined!', 67847, 0), (447093, 'Prosecutors say it would be next to impossible to get one teen to testify in court that another had slipped him or her a copied disc at lunchtime. And besides, isn''t sharing music a time-honored part of teen friendship?', 11321, 0), (447094, 'Growing up, I had an internal struggle with my body because I was really chubby. My sisters were younger, and they were all skinny and all cute. As a teen, I definitely had, like, an extra 30 pounds of weight.', 67850, 0), (447095, 'People now tell me it''s a good thing I stayed away from teen films. Well, it wasn''t my choice. I wasn''t hired.', 68913, 0), (447096, 'If a movie isn''t a hit right out of the gate, they drop it. Which means that the whole mainstream Hollywood product has been skewed toward violence and vulgar teen comedy.', 3723, 0), (447097, 'I think anybody who''s doing work in their teen years on TV or in the movies, you''re a teen idol by default.', 58696, 0), (447098, 'People still come up to me and say, ''Hey, ''Teen Wolf!'' ''Teen Wolf Too'' closed a week after it opened. Where did they see it?', 58696, 0), (447099, 'In my teen years, I was hanging out with adults - Steven Meisel, Francois Nars, Oribe, Paul Cavaco. We had so much fun! We''d go out in New York.', 69119, 0), (447100, 'There''s always a Justin Bieber. Ever since I''ve been around, there''s always been one of him. You know, you can trace it back from how old you are and the boy bands that came along then and the teen sensations and whatnot. And, you know, good for them. There''s a few of them that make it out and a few of them that don''t.', 67013, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447101, 'Once a teen has been identified as part of the ''target market,'' he knows he''s done for. The object of the game is to confound the marketers, and keep one''s own, authentic culture from showing up at the shopping mall as a prepackaged corporate product.', 13581, 0), (447102, 'Let us develop an agenda for children that says we can do something about teen pregnancy. Let us make sure that parents are old enough, wise enough, and financially able to take care of their children.', 65233, 0), (447103, 'Ric Flair was such a huge part of my childhood and teen years. He''s an icon.', 69332, 0), (447104, 'My kids idea of a hard life is to live in a house with only one phone.', 26132, 0), (447105, 'I so think it''s limiting to define an audience ahead of time. This is something I''ve brought on myself by being like, ''There are no ''real'' teen publications! That''s what I''ll do!'' But then it''s like, well, if I want ''Rookie'' to be successful and popular, then people will invalidate the realness by saying it''s popular and mainstream.', 32663, 0), (447106, '''Rookie'' is not your guide to Being a Teen. It is, quite simply, a bunch of writing and art we like and believe in.', 32663, 0), (447107, 'I instinctively dress a bit tougher because I''ve spent a lot of time in the U.S. and I realised there was a certain image projected of me here. I''ve always been an absolute rebel. When I was in my teen years I had piercings and wore all black.', 16756, 0), (447108, 'I was a handful growing up.', 68919, 0), (447109, 'There was a three-year chunk as a teen where I should have been tranquilized and put in a cage.', 28488, 0), (447110, 'I built my entire career off of teen comedies. I was in ''Bring It On''.', 68430, 0), (447111, 'Guilty pleasure implies that it''s something that I feel guilty for watching... people tell me I should feel guilty for watching because I''m too old to watch it, but I don''t give a damn: I love everything on Cartoon Network from ''Adventure Time'' to ''The Adventures of Gumball'', ''Teen Titans''... all those shows that are for my kids, I like those!', 55326, 0), (447112, 'Doesn''t matter whether it''s a teen girl who''s pregnant, hasn''t told her parents, or an elderly couple dealing with one of them being diagnosed with Alzheimer''s. Those are real people to me. Those are the people I dealt with every single day.', 17681, 0), (447113, 'For the youth, the indignation of most things will just surge as each birthday passes.', 23824, 0), (447114, 'When I found out I had to take off my shirt in ''Teen'' movie, I panicked and hit the gym. I was like, ''It''s going to be on film, documented, for my children to see. I can''t be 140 pounds. I need to put on a little bit of muscle.''', 23824, 0), (447115, 'Costumes say a lot about a character. When it came to ''Palo Alto,'' it was important for me that the kids didn''t look perfect. In most teen movies today, all of the clothes are expensive. I remember wearing a lot of dirty vintage clothes.', 69323, 0), (447116, 'Mrs. Palin is history in a dress. And her script is straight out of Hollywood - like those teen movies with the cliched ending featuring the female valedictorian delivering the speech of a lifetime projecting a bold and transformative future with an independent-minded woman in charge.', 17895, 0), (447117, 'Lesley Gore''s part-time field was pop singer, and in her brief but urgent prime, she was the Queen of Teen Angst. She endured heartbreak as a birthday girl betrayed by her beau in ''It''s My Party,'' savored revenge in the sequel ''Judy''s Turn to Cry'' and belted the proto-feminist anthem ''You Don''t Own Me.''', 67854, 0), (447118, 'Fifth grade was when I first heard ''Smells Like Teen Spirit;'' it was the energy, and his voice. I liked 311 and Sublime, too, though that might have been a little after that.', 68262, 0), (447119, 'I was a teen star. That''s disgusting enough.', 70232, 0), (447120, 'As a precocious teen I dreamed of being Graham Greene. Well, as it turned out, I never wrote a great novel, sadly, and I never converted to Catholicism, happily, but I did do one thing he did. That is, in middle age I moved to a seaside town and got into a right barney with the local powers-that-be.', 28504, 0), (447121, 'All that stuff - ''teen idol'' - that wasn''t me.', 70631, 0), (447122, 'Just do me a favor. Don''t call me ''former teen heartthrob,'' okay? It''s as if they were constantly discussing your second year of college. I''m not back there anymore. I''m living in the present.', 70631, 0), (447123, 'I love being in a public space where teenagers are talking. And the funny thing is that it hasn''t changed that much. There''s certainly slang that I''m not familiar with, but among the average teen, it''s still the same.', 2308, 0), (447124, 'I definitely think there could be stricter teen driving laws.', 16615, 0), (447125, 'To even be called the ''teen queen'' is crazy.', 16615, 0), (447126, 'I really liked ''Starter For Ten'' because I grew up watching 1980s teen films like ''St. Elmo''s Fire'' and ''The Breakfast Club'' and I''ve always wanted to play the underdog lead hero in a 1980s-inspired film.', 70221, 0), (447127, 'I never listened to the Grateful Dead as a teen the only exposure I got was what came through the walls when my sister was listening to them. ', 71035, 0), (447128, 'I''d never made a teen comedy in my life.', 68012, 0), (447129, 'Children born to teens have less supportive and stimulating environments, poorer health, lower cognitive development, and worse educational outcomes. Children of teen mothers are at increased risk of being in foster care and becoming teen parents themselves, thereby repeating the cycle.', 64250, 0), (447130, 'If we as a nation are to break the cycle of poverty, crime and the growing underclass of young people ill equipped to be productive citizens, we need to not only implement effective programs to prevent teen pregnancy, but we must also help those who have already given birth so that they become effective, nurturing, bonding parents.', 64250, 0), (447131, 'Clothes are like a suit of armour when you''re young. I was quite a shy teen, so I wanted to make aggressive statements with the way I looked. I''d say my goth/indie stage was the worst: there was a lot of experimentation involving pink food dye in my fringe.', 70672, 0), (447132, 'I want to help middle-school girls stay interested in math and be good at it, and see it as friendly and accessible and not this scary thing. Everyone else in society tells them it''s not for them. It''s for nerdy white guys with pocket protectors.', 66799, 0), (447133, 'I hate it when people call me a teen queen.', 67763, 0), (447134, 'I''ve always enjoyed teen characters, and kids as well. For whatever reason, I seem to have an ability to do it sort of well, and I enjoy doing it.', 61316, 0), (447135, 'I was a total metal-head as a teen. I still love it, too.', 71578, 0), (447136, 'When I was in the 12th grade, I got my girlfriend pregnant. I just got out of school, she was a 10th-grader. I''m a teen parent, and I''m at a point where I''m like, ''Man I''ve got to do something.''', 11834, 0), (447137, 'When I started out as a music journalist, at the end of the 1980s, it was generally assumed that we were living through the lamest music era the world would ever see. But those were also the years when hip-hop exploded, beatbox disco soared, indie rock took off, and new wave invented a language of teen angst.', 340, 0), (447138, 'The area of teenage life is not necessarily rarefied; we''ve all gone through that period. It''s not as rarefied as a western or a space adventure or a gangster film, but it has its own dynamic.', 61609, 0), (447139, 'I see it as more of a teenage activity than, you know, she''s only 11, but you know, I think it''s great that she knows so many girls who want to play music. And I see it more as a teen activity than I do as going into music.', 13347, 0), (447140, 'Typically, middle-class educated parents'' search for their children''s schools takes on the feel, if not of teen girls trying on different outfits, of adolescents trying on various selves.', 70445, 0), (447141, 'I''ve always gravitated towards those ultimate lines in songs, the line you grab on to. That line in ''Smells Like Teen Spirit,'' ''Here we are now/Entertain us'' - the irony, the antagonism; that''s always stuck with me.', 1385, 0), (447142, 'The United States has made remarkable progress in reducing both teen pregnancy and racial and ethnic differences, but the reality is, too many American teens are still having babies.', 67068, 0), (447143, 'They were marketing me as a teen idol, when the stuff on the record was not what teen idols were doing at the time.', 69514, 0), (447144, 'I mean, I''m pretty good in real life, but sometimes people seem surprised that I''m like a normal teenager and wear black nail polish and I''m just a little bit more edgy than the person I play on television.', 70688, 0), (447145, 'People love teen movies because everyone can relate.', 68464, 0), (447146, 'People don''t know the real me. The hard times I went through are what led me to my life now. I was a mess as a teen! I was kind of wild and really unhappy.', 68954, 0), (447147, 'I just fell into the job as a fashion editor at a teen magazine. I was there for two years, and I left there as a senior fashion editor at the age of 25.', 71579, 0), (447148, 'Obviously when you''re a teen you have no money, so you make, like, three outfits out of one dress. You''re like, ''OK cut the arms here. Alright: New party, cut them to here.''', 68466, 0), (447149, 'I grew up in Detroit. I was a teen father. I lived on welfare for three years. I have a brother serving life in prison, though I believe he''s innocent.', 3861, 0), (447150, 'Well, I could do it for a day, but I wouldn''t want to be a teenager again. I really wouldn''t.', 47322, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447151, 'I didn''t want to be the typical teen idol. I didn''t want to be Leif Garrett. I didn''t want to be Shaun Cassidy, David Cassidy or Parker Stevenson. I wanted to do my own thing.', 38165, 0), (447152, 'Being a teen idol or being a heartthrob on all the magazines, with Shaun Cassidy, Leif Garrett, and Scott Baio - it was embarrassing! I never understood it. I mean, why me? I never really got it.', 38165, 0), (447153, 'I found my niche as a character actor, and I''ve never felt like a movie star or teen idol and never wanted to.', 71580, 0), (447154, 'When I was a teenager, I read a lot of Poe.', 68232, 0), (447155, 'I will say that I know Nirvana did a show and played a few chords from ''More Than a Feeling'' before they did ''Teen Spirit,'' and it wasn''t very good. But in all seriousness, ''Teen Spirit'' was a great song. If subconsciously or somehow I had any influence on that, I''ll take that as a compliment.', 67492, 0), (447156, 'Most of the offers I get from Hollywood are for teen comedies. My manager thinks I''m crazy for turning down all that money, but I''m very picky.', 70269, 0), (447157, 'I was into all kinds of music as a teen - country music, because my dad was in a band that played country, and whatever my sister and brother were into.', 7802, 0), (447158, 'If you were an optimistic teen, then you''ll be an optimist at 80. People''s reactions to bad events are highly stable over a half century or more.', 67434, 0), (447159, 'I don''t think there''s a problem with being a teen idol, if that happens to me, I''ll be happy to deal with it.', 71581, 0), (447160, 'I wasn''t going to have fun doing a teen movie again.', 53389, 0), (447161, 'As a kid, I was definitely a DC guy. I started reading big time in the ''80s at the height of the Wolfman/Perez ''New Teen Titans.'' That was definitely the book that hooked me.', 56276, 0), (447162, 'I went on an audition once for a show, and the feedback was to play an angry teen. My agent convinced me to try out. I was really bitter for a while, because it sucks when you don''t get good scripts after working on good quality.', 71582, 0), (447163, 'Heredity is what sets the parents of a teenager wondering about each other.', 2120, 0), (447164, 'Watching ''CSI: Miami'' is like watching ''Teen Jeopardy!'' or doing the crossword puzzle in ''People'' magazine. It makes you feel smart even when you''re not.', 70639, 0), (447165, 'Teen authors love to flirt with taboo, to grapple - sensitively - with dark and frightening issues, and there is nothing darker and more frightening than cancer.', 18722, 0), (447166, 'The phrase ''teen hottie'' literally makes me want to throw up.', 14534, 0), (447167, 'I think I am too old to be doing teen movies. I am just kind of annoyed, because you have all these teen movies coming out with usually either Lindsay Lohan or Hilary Duff doing four of the exact teen movies over and over again.', 71583, 0), (447168, 'I wanted to be a writer as a teen... so storytelling was my first love. In my late teens, design became an obsession as I realized that I could express myself through the medium. Much later, when I founded Fuseproject in 1999, our slogan became ''design brings stories to life.''', 68768, 0), (447169, 'How the original ''Cosmos'' affected me personally was long-term. I wasn''t born early enough to see the original series, but after getting a hold of it in my teen years, it was one of the driving forces behind my passion for science.', 68972, 0), (447170, 'In my teen years leading up to the Olympics, I loved having the excuse to skip out on parties because of skating. Partying wasn''t my thing anyway. Mostly I hung out with other skaters. We were all buddies, so it''s not like I missed out on socializing. I was really enjoying myself.', 67384, 0), (447171, 'Before my teen years, I was losing my hearing pretty quickly, and I was getting very, very angry. I was beginning to become an angry person because of that.', 69522, 0), (447172, 'I think there''s a time in your life where you don''t feel like you fit in. I think everyone has that when you''re a teenager, especially, and especially in the society we live in.', 71584, 0), (447173, 'I didn''t have a teen age at all. I didn''t even look at boys, never mind... then suddenly it was like, ''Oh my god!'' So I made up for a lot of lost time very quickly. It was kind of bonkers. Working hard, partying hard - but also experiencing life, you know.', 67574, 0), (447174, 'I started wearing all black around the time I got into Nirvana. I first heard ''Smells Like Teen Spirit'' when I was about 12, and I remember jumping on my bed, so excited about it.', 71585, 0), (447175, 'Being a musician since I was a teen, Guitar Center is the staple. You need anything to create, it''s there. You need a Guitar Center. You gotta give it homage. It''s a tool shed, and without the tool shed, it''s hard to create.', 71315, 0), (447176, 'I will be able to look back on my teen years as spent on a television set just having the biggest bunch of fun.', 71586, 0), (447177, 'I had teen angst for a while, but I think every teenager has the angst.', 71587, 0), (447178, 'I tend to like writing long stories in comics. I worked on ''Flash,'' ''Teen Titans'' and ''JSA'' for years. I always like diving into characters.', 2219, 0), (447179, 'My first job in TV was hosting this young teen magazine show, and all these high school teenagers showed up from all over Sacramento, California, and they chose four of us to host the show, two boys and two girls. And of the two girls, I was kind of the perky smart one and the other girl was the pretty one.', 67435, 0), (447180, 'Everybody is a teenage idol.', 70729, 0), (447181, 'I played teen roles until high definition came out, and I could never understand it. I would go in for adult roles and be older than many of the people auditioning, but they''d cast the girl without a line on her face.', 68505, 0), (447182, 'I actually love writing for teens best. I had such an awful time in my own teen years - I love having the chance to relive them through my fiction.', 910, 0), (447183, 'The donning of the ear buds marks the beginning of teen life, when children set off on their own for the passage through adolescence.', 45206, 0), (447184, 'I grew up in a house where nobody had to tell me to go to school every day and do my homework.', 71588, 0), (447185, 'I had no idea of the size of my bank account as a teen, and I didn''t care to know. That was my mom''s job, I figured that I would just find out when I turned 18. If you can''t trust your mom, then who can you trust?', 70075, 0), (447186, 'It seems like whenever a big newspaper or TV show talks about teen literature, they focus on dark books or vampire books. It''s kind of this cliche. It seems like the only time adults pay attention is with that angle.', 212, 0), (447187, 'Teenagers are asking, ''Who am I?'' and ''How do I fit in?'' in every aspect of their lives, and the best YA romances appreciate that there is more to a teen''s life than finding love.', 6507, 0), (447188, '''Teen Moms!'' I started watching them like the first two seasons, and I stopped. I stopped because they are too young. I feel sorry for them. And I didn''t watch that show ''Hoarders.'' That thing would made my skin crawl.', 69062, 0), (447189, 'I first read Harper Lee''s ''To Kill a Mockingbird'' as a teen in school, like you did. I read the book alone, eating lunch at my locker, neatly scored oranges my mother divided into five lines with a circle at the top, so my fingers could dig more easily into the orange skin. To this day, the smell of oranges reminds me of ''Mockingbird.''', 630, 0), (447190, 'The eight months I took off between ''Teen Vogue'' and ''Lucky'' afforded me such amazing opportunities, and I learned so much from so many different people - the brands that I worked with, the companies that I was consulting for.', 66927, 0), (447191, 'I wanted to be with the kind of people I''d grown up with, but you can''t go back to them and be one of them again, no matter how hard you try.', 70197, 0), (447192, 'I think the feeling was that ''Venture Brothers'' really has something to sell in terms of a feature. ''Aqua Teen'' is an element minute cartoon, and its very subversive and non sequitur and weird. We were writing the one show where we were constantly like, ''God, I wish we had another hour to tell this story.'' It seemed like a natural fit.', 71589, 0), (447193, 'Katy Perry still gets me every time. She''s very funny in person! We met at the Teen Choice Awards and she pulled my cheeks apart and told me how cute I was. My life was literally flashing before my eyes!', 387, 0), (447194, '''Teen Spirit'' is a celebration of the power that music can deliver to the cinematic experience.', 71590, 0), (447195, 'What''s great about teen fiction is that it''s all mixed up - there''s highbrow and lowbrow!', 436, 0), (447196, 'As I got older, I had a bunch of friends that were various teen stars. I''ve always known people in the spotlight and people who just grew up in L.A. and had nothing to do with the industry. It''s not a glamorous thing to me. It''s just a different type of business.', 71591, 0), (447197, 'I''m not a teen anymore, but growing up, some of my favorite things were, like, ''Twin Peaks,'' which wasn''t even really my time, and this is one of the things, like a weird, quirky, small town mystery.', 71591, 0), (447198, 'I spent the first fourteen years of my life convinced that my looks were hideous. Adolescence is painful for everyone, I know, but mine was plain weird.', 69155, 0), (447199, 'I saw myself as an outsider as a teen. I was home-schooled and got my G.E.D. when I was 16 I wasn''t interested in high school at all and figured that college might be more entertaining. ', 184, 0), (447200, 'When I was a teen, I thought I would have to choose between my writing or my music or my art, but it turns out it''s a difficult juggling game but I can do all of them.', 184, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447201, 'I wouldn''t say I''m stuck in my adolescence, but I think, like a lot of people, I carry my teen years with me. I feel really in touch with those feelings, and how intense and complicated life seems in those years.', 728, 0), (447202, 'I think there are worse things for a teen to be enraptured with than ''Twilight.''', 67128, 0), (447203, 'I just felt being part of my peer group so strongly. I was immersed in teen culture, but not taken in by it.', 1433, 0), (447204, 'I don''t know if this is too weird to say, but this is completely surreal for me. Bizarre. The cover of ''Teen Vogue'' has been on my bucket list forever.', 47780, 0), (447205, 'I think growing up is difficult and it''s a process that I''m always interested in, with kids and adults, they are often on two different universes.', 304, 0), (447206, 'Time misspent in youth is sometimes all the freedom one ever has.', 6358, 0), (447207, 'Growing up, I''ve enjoyed hunting with my father.', 69664, 0), (447208, 'I was a quiet teenager, introverted, full of angst.', 44007, 0), (447209, 'Since my teen years I was interested in martial arts.', 68542, 0), (447210, 'The most important role models should and could be parents and teachers. But that said, once you''re a teenager you''ve probably gotten as much of an example from your parents as you''re going to.', 68032, 0), (447211, 'If you can get a teen leader in each sector of a student population, you can pull people in. Everybody wants to get involved, but most are too afraid. When they see a person they think is cool leading it, they''re first to join.', 68032, 0), (447212, 'I got the acting bug really young, when I was around, like, 10. I pretty much just wanted to be Michael J. Fox. He was in ''Teen Wolf'' - that was, like, the coolest role, and then he did ''Back to the Future,'' and that was the coolest role.', 71592, 0), (447213, 'I was, like, this token teen angst child of Broadway. It''s so funny. What is that? I don''t even know. But I loved it.', 69318, 0), (447214, 'One of my first paid gigs was writing psychology quizzes for ''YM,'' a monthly teen magazine like ''Seventeen.''', 42890, 0), (447215, 'When I was a teen, I was never really into the captain of the football team or the student body president. The guys I liked were quirky and different: They listened to music I''d never heard of, never had lunch or gas money, and could always make you laugh.', 16, 0), (447216, 'I love writing about the summer between high school and college. It''s the last gasp of really being a teen.', 16, 0), (447217, 'When I started writing, there was nothing about zombies. It was all teen movies, which to me are scarier than zombies, but that''s another story.', 3177, 0), (447218, 'A surprising number of American skyjackers were not yet old enough to drink or sometimes even drive. These adolescents were generally inept at planning their crimes, and few of their capers met with any success; most seemed to end within moments of starting, usually after a fatherly pilot convinced the nervous teen to hand over his gun.', 71593, 0), (447219, 'I''m definitely of the ''Harry Potter''-transfigured-me-into-a-reader-and-writer generation. And that''s really all I read throughout my teen years, because I really devoted all my time to writing and reading friends'' fan-fiction.', 5888, 0), (447220, 'I don''t like being compared to anyone or being in a class with someone. I''m a teen actress and therefore I''m competing against Hilary Duff. We''re different people like everyone else.', 71594, 0), (447221, 'The Teen Challenge ministry was born out of those humble early days of ministry. It now includes over 500 drug and alcohol rehab centers around the world, even in Muslim countries. These include homes for girls and women addicts and alcoholics, all which are reaching many.', 9165, 0), (447222, 'The Teen Challenge Training Center on Pennsylvania farmland houses over 200 men in rehab. Other farms and centers have been birthed out of this ministry all over the world.', 9165, 0), (447223, 'I am not officially involved now in the direction of the Teen Challenge ministry, but I rejoice that God permits me to be the father of these ministries.', 9165, 0), (447224, 'Every Teen Challenge ministry is responsible for raising its own finances, but we assist these works with finances, prayer and counseling, especially overseas in areas such as Siberia, Africa, South America.', 9165, 0), (447225, 'If you were an alien who came to our bookstores - or browsed our teen magazines - you''d think that only Earth girls who look like Mila Kunis ever got any action.', 54, 0), (447226, 'The eighties were my teen years, so the GoGos are sort of a touchstone.', 71595, 0), (447227, 'My first break was becoming a staff writer on the rebooted ''90210.'' And then I got stuck writing in the teen genre for a while.', 71111, 0), (447228, 'This may just be me, but I feel like everyone''s dream is to live as an American high school student. There are so many teen films set in America that you live vicariously through them, anyway.', 71596, 0), (447229, 'At the age of 16 I was already dreaming of having a baby because I felt myself to be an adult, but my mum forbid it. Right now, I feel like a teenager and I want to have fun for one or two more years before starting a family.', 71292, 0), (447230, 'Growing up, I didn''t have a lot of toys, and personal entertainment depended on individual ingenuity and imagination - think up a story and go live it for an afternoon.', 1943, 0), (447231, 'Can you imagine young people nowadays making a study of trigonometry for the fun of it? Well I did.', 69955, 0), (447232, 'I got through my teen years by being a bit of a clown.', 71597, 0), (447233, 'I was never interested in ''Teen Beat'' like roles. I just wanted to work.', 5191, 0), (447234, 'Certain elements of teen life that, 10 years ago, were very important to me still, are becoming less so as I get older. I mean, I''ve kinda gotten over, I guess I''m saying, the fact that I had trouble getting a date for the prom.', 71598, 0), (447235, 'I think I''m also more open to other writers being present and listening to other opinions, whereas before I was going through my angsty teen years while making records.', 71599, 0), (447236, 'Teen movies often have an unspoken underlying premise in which high school is seen as less serious than the adult world. But when your head is encased in that microcosm it''s the most serious time of your life.', 71600, 0), (447237, 'I was a typical Valley teen, in smoggy Van Nuys.', 71601, 0), (447238, 'I was a typical teen growing up in the 1960s, when everybody was into gurus and meditation.', 70433, 0), (447239, 'If you try to bring ''teen drama,'' you end up doing nothing but pouting.', 68372, 0), (447240, 'We all have an interest in making sure teens grow up healthy and drug-free.', 43931, 0), (447241, 'Teen drug use went up dramatically in the 1990s.', 43931, 0), (447242, 'Research shows that parents are the single biggest influence on children - if you are worried about your teen and drugs, talk to them.', 43931, 0), (447243, 'I have been in teen shows for years, so doing that stuff - kissing - is kind of commonplace and not a big deal. It was way more cool just because it was Meg Ryan.', 69401, 0), (447244, 'I decided that, if I were to write a teen series, I''d want to set it in a place that was familiar to me - Manhattan, where I''d grown up - and I''d model the characters on myself and my friends.', 690, 0), (447245, 'Teen problem novels? I can go through them like a box of chocolates. And there are fantasy books out now that need a lot more editing. Fantasy got to be so popular that people began to think ''We don''t need to be as diligent with the razor blade,'' but they do.', 2177, 0), (447246, 'Final Destination was the closest thing I''ve done to a teen movie but it certainly had an edge to it.', 69088, 0), (447247, 'If I can write a book that will help the world make a little more sense to a teen, then that''s why I was put on the planet.', 1421, 0), (447248, 'Yeah, I spent my teen years in West Virginia, and when I was a kid, in Louisiana. I definitely have that exposure to two different sorts of rural: the South and Appalachia.', 71602, 0), (447249, 'Well, I actually first got into music as a small child, and as I became a teen, I sought out making money from music, weather that was singing lounge gigs, backup in studios, or weddings.', 71603, 0), (447250, 'I can have a song with Ariana Grande that is going to be the song for all the kids and the teen girls, and then another song that could be for a different group of people who all love the song. I''m with whoever. Whatever type of people want to love the music and whatever they love about the music is fine with me.', 1630, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447251, 'I did try to get a few of those teen high-school movies, but they just didn''t like me. I guess I wasn''t a certain type.', 71604, 0), (447252, 'Frank Sinatra is the only one that went from teen idol to superstar.', 71605, 0), (447253, 'I took high school very casually. There was Teen Town, chess, tennis, boxing, running. Lots of things going on.', 71606, 0), (447254, 'I remember as a teen being able to eat more than my father. I was growing so fast and my body couldn''t keep up.', 70569, 0), (447255, 'I''d like a pop-up magazine with 45 articles on Russell Crowe. I''m like a teenager. I''d have ''Teen Beat'' if I could, for grown-ups.', 62986, 0), (447256, '''Snowpiercer'' is a little bit more experimental, I think, and crafted for a slightly different audience. ''The Giver'' is more about teen angst.', 71607, 0), (447257, 'The average teen today spends about 35 hours a week in front of a screen of some kind: iPod, movie, TV, video. And a lot of it is good, but a lot of it''s not. And so I think you''ve got that five hours a day of media coming into your kid''s head that''s creating a lot of havoc out there.', 6058, 0), (447258, 'To be honest, I haven''t seen a lot of the current crop of teen movies because there''s only so much time and there''s nothing that really drives me to do it.', 71608, 0), (447259, 'Ever since I was a little teen, I was told by my great-grandma that you''ve got to always have a good moisturizer. I use cocoa butter, and I use it for all things needing moisture - face, hair, throw it on those legs at the beach, get them all shiny. Cocoa butter is such a great product.', 71609, 0), (447260, 'I consider myself a writer. I always wanted to act, and as a teen, I studied acting devotedly. Eventually, I got writing work, but very little acting work.', 68320, 0), (447261, 'A fairly bright boy is far more intelligent and far better company than the average adult.', 70962, 0), (447262, 'Writing a teen character is something I wanted to try again for a long time!', 303, 0), (447263, 'Yes, but I don''t think of the Teen Angel as of an age.', 71610, 0), (447264, 'I don''t want to just be in the normal kind of teen movie.', 71611, 0), (447265, 'Robin McKinley''s ''The Blue Sword'' was a defining book of my teen years, and I''d love to have more books like that in the world.', 2305, 0), (447266, 'I don''t usually like teen novels written in the present tense, particularly those told from a first-person viewpoint. Too many writers seem to believe that using either or both devices automatically imbues their stories with deep seriousness and a contemporary feel.', 70247, 0), (447267, 'I''m so fascinated by the concept of teen pregnancy for some reason. Not that I condone it or promote it, but it''s just a very real thing in our country and culture.', 71612, 0), (447268, 'Material Girls was so different for me, I''d never done a teen movie.', 71613, 0), (447269, 'The first time I got pregnant, I was a young girl - I was 17 years old. Although I knew right away that I wanted to keep my child, being a pregnant teen was an extremely scary experience for me. Luckily, my family and friends were very supportive and were there for me every step of the way.', 71614, 0), (447270, 'Nobody understands anyone 18, including those who are 18.', 20146, 0), (447271, 'As I''ve said many times, the single most oppressed class in America right now is the teenager.', 71615, 0), (447272, 'I''ve never done a teen movie before, but I certainly could tell you some of the ones I came very close on. I was very close on Clueless and She''s All That.', 8307, 0), (447273, 'I grew up in a small town in Kansas, so I love meeting the fans. Those are the people who spend time out of their day to watch the things that I''ve done, and I''ve gotten to do some great supernatural stuff - ''Teen Wolf'' and ''The Gates'' before that - so it''s nice when I get to go to Comic-Con every year.', 66986, 0), (447274, 'I think doing ''Teen Wolf'' is just giving me a really great opportunity to possibly get other jobs and show what I can do.', 66986, 0), (447275, 'I think the fans from the original ''Teen Wolf'' tuned in expecting us to ruin the franchise, and I think that we''ve only heightened it. So we''ve brought ''Teen Wolf'' back.', 66986, 0), (447276, 'To be honest, and this is terrible to admit, I hardly read any teen mystery books at all.', 57257, 0), (447277, 'I absolutely adore classic crime and read a huge amount as a teen - Agatha Christie, Dorothy L. Sayers, Sherlock Holmes, Josephine Tey, and many more.', 29236, 0), (447278, 'But when I was a teenager, the idea of spending the rest of my life in a factory was real depressing. So the idea that I could become a musician opened up some possibilities I didn''t see otherwise.', 71616, 0), (447279, 'I take mentoring very seriously and I am on the board of an organization called Girls Write Now, where we match teen girls and writing mentors because it changes their lives.', 12486, 0), (447280, 'I think there''s actually a benefit to working with teen actors: they''ve got such boundless energy, and everybody is willing to try different things.', 71617, 0), (447281, 'As a white teen, I was very drawn to hip-hop culture, almost to the point of disappearing in it - there was a sense of having no sense of authenticity except this one that wasn''t mine.', 28687, 0), (447282, 'I love being a teen because you don''t have all the responsibilities of an adult yet.', 68637, 0), (447283, 'I don''t want to be a ''teen star'' because so many people don''t ever grow out of that.', 71618, 0), (447284, 'I did work at a mall in college - I think retail/customer service is just one of the most hideous jobs in the world. So I always try to be extra nice when I go into a store. But malls are part of our culture, if you watched any teen comedy in the ''80s. it''s clear that malls are where we live!', 71619, 0), (447285, 'When I was growing up, particularly during puberty in my teen years, I was so miserable because I elicited so much teasing and meanness from my teenage cohorts.', 71620, 0), (447286, 'The distinction has blurred between young adult and adult books. Some of the teen books have become more sophisticated.', 256, 0), (447287, 'Cartoons are the best stuff on TV. ''Wonder Showzen,'' ''Aqua Teen,'' ''SpongeBob,'' and, of course, ''South Park'' - one of the funniest shows ever made.', 71621, 0), (447288, 'I write edgy, sexy teen romances, and that''s what I''ll continue to do.', 200, 0), (447289, '''Teen Beach Movie'' was a lot of fun because we were in Puerto Rico on an island - you can''t even call it work!', 35810, 0), (447290, 'I have always had a sense that we are all pretty much alone in life, particularly in adolescence.', 1587, 0), (447291, 'In the Top 40, half the songs are secret messages to the teen world to drop out, turn on, and groove with the chemicals and light shows at discotheques.', 71622, 0), (447292, 'I''m a teen boy, so I like seeing blood and guts. I know it''s fake, but I''m having fun.', 71623, 0), (447293, 'You need to know what makes artists tick. Having been through the process myself as a musician, since I was an early teen, gave me an advantage - understanding them from their point of view, because it''s about them, it''s not about you - it''s their vision and what they''re capable of achieving, and you''re the conduit.', 71624, 0), (447294, 'And at some point I would like to talk my publisher into doing an anthology of my poetry alongside some teen readers'' poetry. It would be fun, and really wonderful to get their stuff out there.', 431, 0), (447295, 'I didn''t know what was going to happen with ''Teen Wolf.'' I was only scheduled to do four episodes for them, but they kept me on, and I was like, ''Sweet! I''m still employed! That''s awesome!'' And then, they let me know that they were considering having me for the second half of the season.', 71625, 0), (447296, 'I''m still good friends with everybody from ''Teen Wolf.'' I still see them, and I go to Jeff Davis'' for ''Teen Wolf'' night when I can. It was such a rewarding experience. That''s such a fun set.', 71625, 0), (447297, 'I pass on a lot of teen roles that get sent to me because a lot of the time it doesn''t feel real. It''s sugar-coated. There''s no depth to it.', 71626, 0), (447298, 'I started a MySpace teen lit discussion group and invited people to join.', 11825, 0), (447299, 'I watch a lot of teen TV and read a lot of YA novels. I also talk to teens whenever I can. There are cultural differences between when I was a teen and now, but emotions - anger, angst, love - are the same.', 11825, 0), (447300, 'Maybe that''s the whole teen oeuvre, you know covering people in disgusting bodily fluids and whatnot.', 71627, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447301, 'My high school years were fun and frustrating, typical of the teen years. The most important accomplishment was meeting my wife, Ruth.', 71628, 0), (447302, 'I''m pretty sure this is it for the teen movie thing. It''s so frustrating to read when you get to page 20 and you''re like, Oy! It''s the same thing again!', 71629, 0), (447303, 'I love being a part of Aqua Teen.', 70481, 0), (447304, 'I''ve always enjoyed the teen angst thing. I had a lot of teen angst as I was growing up, so I think I have a lot to say about it through characters before I have to move on.', 71630, 0), (447305, 'Just because you have teenagers in a movie doesn''t make it a teen movie.', 71631, 0), (447306, 'Being a teen is past for me. Worrying about the world and my place in it is not.', 337, 0), (447307, 'I could have been on a path that led to different, more traditional teen romance, and ''Nip/Tuck'' shook me loose from any generalization I might have been forced into. It helped me understand I wanted to take on things that were edgier, more challenging and riskier.', 71632, 0), (447308, 'There''s a theory about fame: the moment it strikes, it arrests development. Michael Jackson remained suspended in childhood, enjoying sleepovers and funfairs; Winona Ryder, an errant teen who dabbled in shoplifting and experimented with pills; George Clooney, a 30-year-old commitment-phobe, never quite ready yet to settle down.', 71633, 0), (447309, 'It''s always good to get feedback from people. I''ve been fortunate that all the fans, and especially fans of ''Teen Wolf,'' have been really gracious.', 71634, 0), (447310, 'Of course Stephen King doesn''t believe in teen novels. I''ve started to suspect he doesn''t even believe in teenagers.', 3748, 0), (447311, 'Teen fiction should be about teenagers - no matter how many arguments there are about what YA lit should be, this seems like the one thing we can all agree on.', 3748, 0), (447312, 'When I turned thirteen and took a typing class, with typical early teen enthusiasm and total lack of critical ability, I started sending my stuff to publishers once I''d babysat long enough to earn the postage.', 3435, 0), (447313, 'Teenagers today are more free to be themselves and to accept themselves.', 4178, 0), (447314, 'I think if we were going to worry about teen pregnancy being glamorized, we should worry about shows like ''Teen Mom''. If people are going to want to have children at a young age because they see it on TV, I think that depends on the type of person you''re dealing with.', 71305, 0), (447315, 'As a unique person, I was bullied badly as a teen.', 71635, 0), (447316, 'When I was 14, I came very close to becoming a gay teen suicide ''statistic,'' but I then turned to music, my piano, my loved ones, and discovered that it does in fact get better.', 71636, 0), (447317, 'I don''t really think I feel pressured to become a teen sensation because that''s not really my goal in life. It''s not really about being star, being popular or having lots of girls. It''s really about continuing to be able to act and have fun, and do what I like to do.', 71637, 0), (447318, 'I do a lot of teen shows and voice over work for animation, so when I got the part in ''The Number 23,'' it was really cool because now I get to be in a movie with Jim Carrey. Acting in this movie was really a learning experience for me.', 71638, 0), (447319, 'I actually hope people don''t react to ''Impossible'' in a way where they think it''s terribly retro. The plot needed to do what it needed to do. But I''m a little surprised to find myself looking a little bit like an advocate of teen marriage. It takes some exceptional circumstances for that to be a reasonable idea.', 7187, 0), (447320, '''Catcher in the Rye.'' I feel like any brooding teen loves that book.', 71639, 0), (447321, 'When I got near teen age, I was so happy with my friends and the African-American culture that I couldn''t imagine not being part of it.', 71640, 0), (447322, 'When I was a freshman, I didn''t have that much time for extra-curriculars, so I didn''t do any theater stuff. Actually, I didn''t do it with my school. I did theater with this thing called Teen Source.', 71641, 0), (447323, 'I progressed through so many different styles of music through my teen years, both as a player and a vocalist, particularly the jazz and pop of the early 20th Century.', 71642, 0), (447324, 'Maturity is only a short break in adolescence.', 10519, 0), (447325, 'My own experience being bullied - it made me a more compassionate person. It made me more sympathetic to the adolescent experience.', 4784, 0), (447326, 'My writing books with positive gay characters has come more out of anger than anything else: anger at not having been able to find honest, accurate books about people like myself as a teen, books that show we''re as diverse as straight people and that we can lead happy, healthy, productive lives just as straight people can.', 25292, 0), (447327, 'Teenage girls read in packs. It''s true today, and it was true when I was a teen growing up in a small town in northeast Oklahoma.', 674, 0), (447328, 'A departure from the movie with Michael J. Fox, ''Teen Wolf'' tells the story of how a group of angsty teens deal with werewolves, their supernatural kin and the world of trouble that comes with it, all while trying to still live their lives.', 70975, 0), (447329, 'It hasn''t been until the last couple years that I''ve started playing close to my age. But it''s fun playing the younger roles because it takes you back to the teen years.', 71643, 0), (447330, 'This is actually something no one knows, but my mom was really the one who created the entire style for ''Teen Witch.'' I''m dead serious. She was super involved, and is super creative, so I wore a lot of my actual clothes in the movie. Truly, Louise was my mom''s vision. She really created an iconic character.', 71644, 0), (447331, 'Because of people like that guy in San Francisco who told me it changed his life, ''Teen Witch'' is my most favorite thing I''ve ever done. I see how happy it makes people, and that makes me happy. The great thing is that no one realized it was going to become all these things when we were making it. We thought we were making a very serious movie.', 71644, 0), (447332, 'My younger sister and younger brother are huge ''Teen Witch'' fans.', 71644, 0), (447333, 'This is actually something no one knows, but my mom was really the one who created the entire style for ''Teen Witch.'' I''m dead serious.', 71644, 0), (447334, 'I think teen girls will like ''Geek Charming'' because they really focus on the ''populars'' and nerdy people and people who are in between the nerds and between the populars. So it really hits every category of what girls are going through in high school.', 71645, 0), (447335, 'There''s an indie movie I did called ''Fat Kid Rules the World,'' which was based on a teen book, and it''s a fabulous story, and hopefully it''ll go to theaters because it is an amazing story.', 71645, 0), (447336, '''Pretty Little Liars,'' you know, it''s a teen show that grew to be something bigger. I think you had girls from ages 7 to, like, 20 watching the show, and that was the predominant audience. Then it grew to be for girls, boys, men, women, people who are 7 to 35. I think that''s crazy.', 71646, 0), (447337, 'The ''Teen Wolf'' fans are so great.', 71647, 0), (447338, 'I was a big fan of black gospel. As a kid, there were black groups I sang with from my teen years to my early 20s.', 71648, 0), (447339, 'Music is probably the only real magic I have encountered in my life. There''s not some trick involved with it. It''s pure and it''s real. It moves, it heals, it communicates and does all these incredible things.', 21291, 0), (447340, 'Music is a moral law. It gives soul to the universe, wings to the mind, flight to the imagination, and charm and gaiety to life and to everything.', 51, 0), (447341, 'To me there is no picture so beautiful as smiling, bright-eyed, happy children; no music so sweet as their clear and ringing laughter.', 34868, 0), (447342, 'Music is a higher revelation than all wisdom and philosophy.', 1791, 0), (447343, 'I think music in itself is healing. It''s an explosive expression of humanity. It''s something we are all touched by. No matter what culture we''re from, everyone loves music.', 1502, 0), (447344, 'The true beauty of music is that it connects people. It carries a message, and we, the musicians, are the messengers.', 71649, 0), (447345, 'Sometimes, being different feels a lot like being alone. But with that being said, being true to that and being true to my standards and my way of doing things in my art and my music, everything that has made me feel very different... in the end, it has made me the happiest.', 22683, 0), (447346, 'If you are a chef, no matter how good a chef you are, it''s not good cooking for yourself; the joy is in cooking for others - it''s the same with music.', 32686, 0), (447347, 'Music, at its essence, is what gives us memories. And the longer a song has existed in our lives, the more memories we have of it.', 2141, 0), (447348, 'Some people ask the secret of our long marriage. We take time to go to a restaurant two times a week. A little candlelight, dinner, soft music and dancing. She goes Tuesdays, I go Fridays.', 11800, 0), (447349, 'Music is the movement of sound to reach the soul for the education of its virtue.', 51, 0), (447350, 'Music washes away from the soul the dust of everyday life.', 65623, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447351, 'Music should strike fire from the heart of man, and bring tears from the eyes of woman.', 1791, 0), (447352, 'Life is one grand, sweet song, so start the music.', 1727, 0), (447353, 'The dance can reveal everything mysterious that is hidden in music, and it has the additional merit of being human and palpable. Dancing is poetry with arms and legs.', 1165, 0), (447354, 'Without music, life is a journey through a desert.', 2045, 0), (447355, 'Music is one of the most powerful things the world has to offer. No matter what race or religion or nationality or sexual orientation or gender that you are, it has the power to unite us.', 47, 0), (447356, 'Mathematics is the music of reason.', 42089, 0), (447357, 'Words make you think a thought. Music makes you feel a feeling. A song makes you feel a thought.', 22663, 0), (447358, 'Music is therapy. Music moves people. It connects people in ways that no other medium can. It pulls heart strings. It acts as medicine.', 16895, 0), (447359, 'Music is the mediator between the spiritual and the sensual life.', 1791, 0), (447360, 'The world is full of poetry. The air is living with its spirit; and the waves dance to the music of its melodies, and sparkle in its brightness.', 71650, 0), (447361, 'I enjoy being happy every day, and hopefully you can hear my happiness in my music. Life is beautiful.', 67850, 0), (447362, 'Complete strangers can stand silent next to each other in an elevator and not even look each other in the eye. But at a concert, those same strangers could find themselves dancing and singing together like best friends. That''s the power of music.', 69154, 0), (447363, 'There''s just a completely different vibe at festivals. Everyone gets to hang out and enjoy their favorite music all day. I really do try and play as many festivals as possible!', 69357, 0), (447364, 'Beautiful music is the art of the prophets that can calm the agitations of the soul it is one of the most magnificent and delightful presents God has given us. ', 1746, 0), (447365, 'There is geometry in the humming of the strings, there is music in the spacing of the spheres.', 464, 0), (447366, 'I call architecture frozen music.', 282, 0), (447367, 'Arts education is a big part of building a 21st century creative mind, and I think that we have let way too many kids lose their way by not drawing in their young minds with music, dance, painting and the other various ways we can express those things we do not have words for.', 71651, 0), (447368, 'Music drives you. It wakes you up, it gets you pumping. And, at the end of the day, the correct tune will chill you down.', 69271, 0), (447369, 'For me, singing sad songs often has a way of healing a situation. It gets the hurt out in the open into the light, out of the darkness.', 1356, 0), (447370, 'Music is life itself. What would this world be without good music? No matter what kind it is.', 22681, 0), (447371, 'Musicians don''t retire they stop when there''s no more music in them. ', 22681, 0), (447372, 'Close friends contribute to our personal growth. They also contribute to our personal pleasure, making the music sound sweeter, the wine taste richer, the laughter ring louder because they are there.', 29209, 0), (447373, 'I was raised in a very humble environment, and I was always taught to be humble to the things that are happening in my life because they''re blessings. They''re blessings in every way. Whether you''re able to help someone get through a tough time in their life through your music or through comedy, or whatever it is, you''re just a channel.', 58477, 0), (447374, 'Music has healing power. It has the ability to take people out of themselves for a few hours.', 1620, 0), (447375, 'As you begin to realize that every different type of music, everybody''s individual music, has its own rhythm, life, language and heritage, you realize how life changes, and you learn how to be more open and adaptive to what is around us.', 25711, 0), (447376, 'I try to apply colors like words that shape poems, like notes that shape music.', 19758, 0), (447377, 'If people take anything from my music, it should be motivation to know that anything is possible as long as you keep working at it and don''t back down.', 392, 0), (447378, 'I''m not a pretty princess, and I''m aware of that, so I like music that is really intense, really bold, and characters that in a way almost have a dark side and are kind of evil because, for me, that''s when I feel my strongest and fiercest, when I''m not necessarily the good girl.', 69757, 0), (447379, 'Sometimes I feel like rap music is almost the key to stopping racism.', 392, 0), (447380, 'I will never forget experiencing Venice for the first time. It feels like you are transported to another time - the art, music, food and pure romance in the air is like no other place.', 71652, 0), (447381, 'Rock and roll music, if you like it, if you feel it, you can''t help but move to it. That''s what happens to me. I can''t help it.''', 1120, 0), (447382, 'I need to listen to chill music when I''m driving. It prevents road rage.', 69751, 0), (447383, 'That''s the amazing thing about music: there''s a song for every emotion. Can you imagine a world with no music? It would suck.', 500, 0), (447384, 'Music is the art of the prophets and the gift of God.', 1746, 0), (447385, 'Having good health, being able to breathe and be happy, that''s one of the most beautiful gifts. On top of that, I have the gift to play music and make people happy through that. I''m just telling you from my heart, I''m so in love with life.', 71649, 0), (447386, 'Hip-hop is the streets. Hip-hop is a couple of elements that it comes from back in the days... that feel of music with urgency that speaks to you. It speaks to your livelihood and it''s not compromised. It''s blunt. It''s raw, straight off the street - from the beat to the voice to the words.', 66586, 0), (447387, 'Music doesn''t lie. If there is something to be changed in this world, then it can only happen through music.', 92, 0), (447388, 'When I die, I want people to play my music, go wild and freak out and do anything they want to do.', 92, 0), (447389, 'I listened, motionless and still; And, as I mounted up the hill, The music in my heart I bore, Long after it was heard no more.', 2063, 0), (447390, 'I love music. It''s freedom, a way to deal with pent-up frustration.', 26404, 0), (447391, 'Each year, every city in the world that can should have a multiday festival. More people meeting each other, digging new types of music, new foods, new ideas. You want to stop having so many wars? This could be a step in the right direction.', 68, 0), (447392, 'Tones sound, and roar and storm about me until I have set them down in notes.', 1791, 0), (447393, 'I was born with music inside me. Music was one of my parts. Like my ribs, my kidneys, my liver, my heart. Like my blood. It was a force already within me when I arrived on the scene. It was a necessity for me - like food or water.', 16427, 0), (447394, 'Like sunshine, music is a powerful force that can instantly and almost chemically change your entire mood.', 21674, 0), (447395, 'There is nothing stable in the world uproar''s your only music. ', 191, 0), (447396, 'Hawaii is paradise. It sounds cheesy to say it, but there''s music in the air there.', 22720, 0), (447397, 'Music should probably provide answers in terms of lyrical content, and giving people a sense of togetherness and oneness, as opposed to being alone in their thoughts and dilemmas or regrets or happiness or whatever.', 69406, 0), (447398, 'That''s why this generation is the least racist generation ever. You see it all the time. Go to any club. People are intermingling, hanging out, having fun, enjoying the same music. Hip-hop is not just in the Bronx anymore. It''s worldwide. Everywhere you go, people are listening to hip-hop and partying together. Hip-hop has done that.', 8650, 0), (447399, 'Those who decide to use leisure as a means of mental development, who love good music, good books, good pictures, good plays, good company, good conversation - what are they? They are the happiest people in the world.', 6067, 0), (447400, 'My body is damaged from music in two ways. I have a red irritation in my stomach. It''s psychosomatic, caused by all the anger and the screaming. I have scoliosis, where the curvature of your spine is bent, and the weight of my guitar has made it worse. I''m always in pain, and that adds to the anger in our music.', 890, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447401, 'Of all the music that reached farthest into heaven, it is the beating of a loving heart.', 2175, 0), (447402, 'Music is an expression of individuality; it''s how you see the world. All art is, for that matter. You take how you experience the world, interpret it, and send it out there - express it - whether it''s sculpture, dance or singing.', 66994, 0), (447403, 'Music comes to me more readily than words.', 1791, 0), (447404, 'Being in Blur has allowed me to travel and hear the music that''s being made all over the world.', 67504, 0), (447405, 'I feel like skateboarding is as much of a sport as a lifestyle, and an art form, so there''s so much that that transcends in terms of music, fashion, and entertainment.', 54545, 0), (447406, 'A film is - or should be - more like music than like fiction. It should be a progression of moods and feelings. The theme, what''s behind the emotion, the meaning, all that comes later.', 7875, 0), (447407, 'To me, movies and music go hand in hand. When I''m writing a script, one of the first things I do is find the music I''m going to play for the opening sequence.', 1484, 0), (447408, 'Music inflames temperament.', 216, 0), (447409, 'My music is the spiritual expression of what I am - my faith, my knowledge, my being.', 19299, 0), (447410, 'Cinematography is infinite in its possibilities... much more so than music or language.', 68354, 0), (447411, 'Fun can happen on the interior. Nobody knows about it, but there are fireworks going on inside your spirit when you hear a great orchestra playing great music.', 70292, 0), (447412, 'I don''t care what people think of me, unless they think I''m mean or something, but I don''t care if they think I''m like someone else because I know I''m not - I''m a total weirdo. I''m not selling a dream; I''m not selling fame like it is some sort of fantastic thing. I''m just trying to sell music and get on with my real life.', 68242, 0), (447413, 'Film is one of the three universal languages, the other two: mathematics and music.', 55471, 0), (447414, 'On the other hand, what I like my music to do to me is awaken the ghosts inside of me. Not the demons, you understand, but the ghosts.', 1232, 0), (447415, 'Music is moonlight in the gloomy night of life.', 62538, 0), (447416, 'The wise musicians are those who play what they can master.', 12781, 0), (447417, 'Basically, radio hasn''t changed over the years. Despite all the technical improvements, it still boils down to a man or a woman and a microphone, playing music, sharing stories, talking about issues - communicating with an audience.', 70712, 0), (447418, 'Music is the harmonious voice of creation an echo of the invisible world. ', 58599, 0), (447419, 'Music is everybody''s possession. It''s only publishers who think that people own it.', 46, 0), (447420, 'The spiral in a snail''s shell is the same mathematically as the spiral in the Milky Way galaxy, and it''s also the same mathematically as the spirals in our DNA. It''s the same ratio that you''ll find in very basic music that transcends cultures all over the world.', 12986, 0), (447421, 'I write while listening to music, mostly because the world beyond my headphones is too chaotic.', 37975, 0), (447422, 'Music is my religion.', 92, 0), (447423, 'People haven''t always been there for me, but music always has.', 100, 0), (447424, 'Adult life is dealing with an enormous amount of questions that don''t have answers. So I let the mystery settle into my music. I don''t deny anything, I don''t advocate anything, I just live with it.', 2251, 0), (447425, 'In string theory, all particles are vibrations on a tiny rubber band; physics is the harmonies on the string; chemistry is the melodies we play on vibrating strings; the universe is a symphony of strings, and the ''Mind of God'' is cosmic music resonating in 11-dimensional hyperspace.', 1821, 0), (447426, 'I basically taught myself how to DJ, but I''ve been inspired by DJs throughout my whole career. I have some good friends that would hook us up with music. You learn some little things here and there from each DJ and you just take it and put your own style into to it.', 71653, 0), (447427, 'There''s nothing better than live music. It''s raw energy, and raw energy feeds the soul.', 20109, 0), (447428, 'Music is the best way for me to say I love you.', 71654, 0), (447429, 'Music washes away the dust of every day life.', 71655, 0), (447430, 'A lot of music is mathematics. It''s balance.', 2237, 0), (447431, 'Gospel music to me has always been a balm for the soul. It has been able to usher in the spirit, usher in worship, true worship and praise, healing. I find the music to be very good at healing and the passion, you know, which is a testimony being told in song.', 71656, 0), (447432, 'People today are still living off the table scraps of the sixties. They are still being passed around - the music and the ideas.', 289, 0), (447433, 'I think the most important thing about music is the sense of escape.', 70078, 0), (447434, 'My music fights against the system that teaches to live and die.', 7, 0), (447435, 'Military justice is to justice what military music is to music.', 1040, 0), (447436, 'I liberate minds with my music. That''s more important than liberating a few people from apartheid or whatever.', 3290, 0), (447437, 'The history of the music industry is inevitably also the story of the development of technology. From the player piano to the vinyl disc, from reel-to-reel tape to the cassette, from the CD to the digital download, these formats and devices changed not only the way music was consumed, but the very way artists created it.', 71657, 0), (447438, 'I found that dance, music, and literature is how I made sense of the world... it pushed me to think of things bigger than life''s daily routines... to think beyond what is immediate or convenient.', 56814, 0), (447439, 'Music is a powerful tool in galvanizing people around an issue. There''s no better way to get your point across than to put it in a beautiful song.', 1451, 0), (447440, 'Jazz music is to be played sweet, soft, plenty rhythm.', 71658, 0), (447441, 'Music is the emotional life of most people.', 571, 0), (447442, 'You have to open your mind. I like the ability to express myself in a deep way. It''s the closest music to our humanity - it''s like a folk music that rises up out of a culture.', 71659, 0), (447443, 'I think the feelings in my music were suggested to me before I even had the ability to play music.', 71660, 0), (447444, 'Yoga is almost like music in a way there''s no end to it. ', 9151, 0), (447445, 'You are the music while the music lasts.', 1067, 0), (447446, 'It''s funny how the music industry is enraged about the Internet and the way things are copied without being paid for. But you know why people steal the music? Because they can''t afford the music.', 21291, 0), (447447, 'If you don''t die of thirst, there are blessings in the desert. You can be pulled into limitlessness, which we all yearn for, or you can do the beauty of minutiae, the scrimshaw of tiny and precise. The sky is your ocean, and the crystal silence will uplift you like great gospel music, or Neil Young.', 457, 0), (447448, 'Bluegrass has brought more people together and made more friends than any music in the world. You meet people at festivals and renew acquaintances year after year.', 71661, 0), (447449, 'Music is therapy for me. It''s my outlet for every negative thing I''ve ever been through. It lets me turn something bad into something beautiful.', 44644, 0), (447450, 'Reggae has a philosophy, you know? It''s not just entertainment. There''s an idea behind it, a way of life behind the music, which is a positive way of life, which is a progressive way of life for better people.', 13964, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447451, 'It''s very strange how electronic music formatted itself and forgot that its roots are about the surprise, freedom, and the acceptance of every race, gender, and style of music into this big party. Instead, it started to become this electronic lifestyle which also involved the glorification of technology.', 69319, 0), (447452, 'If you talk bad about country music, it''s like saying bad things about my momma. Them''s fightin'' words.', 1300, 0), (447453, 'My idea of heaven is a place where the Tyne meets the Delta, where folk music meets the blues.', 7033, 0), (447454, 'Music fills the infinite between two souls.', 430, 0), (447455, 'Where there is devotional music, God is always at hand with His gracious presence.', 1825, 0), (447456, 'Whether looking at pop music, hip-hop or R&B, it''s rare to find an artist who hasn''t been touched or affected by the power and soul of gospel music. In fact, many of today''s popular artists such as Whitney Houston, John Legend, and Katy Perry started their careers in the church choir.', 71662, 0), (447457, 'All music is escapism for me, but I like the way that, on a good night, that sense of escapism can be shared.', 71663, 0), (447458, 'Music is your own experience, your own thoughts, your wisdom. If you don''t live it, it won''t come out of your horn. They teach you there''s a boundary line to music. But, man, there''s no boundary line to art.', 22679, 0), (447459, 'Music became a healer for me. And I learned to listen with all my being. I found that it could wipe away all the emotions of fear and confusion relating to my family.', 3976, 0), (447460, 'Music can name the unnameable and communicate the unknowable.', 2229, 0), (447461, 'Music is a safe kind of high.', 92, 0), (447462, 'I think every revolutionary act is an act of love. Every song that I''ve written, it is because of my desire to use music as a way to empower and re-humanize people who are living in a dehumanizing setting. The song is in order to better the human condition.', 71664, 0), (447463, 'It is so important for people at a young age to be invited to embrace classical music and opera.', 22778, 0), (447464, 'I have been able to tap into all the negative things that can happen to me throughout my life by numbing myself to the pain so to speak and kind of being able to vent it through my music.', 60782, 0), (447465, 'Things can be really empty in this world, and I don''t just mean the music world. It can become a very meaningless place if you don''t really understand: ''who am I? Why am I here? What am I doing?'' To feel fulfilment and have a deeper level of understanding, personally, that is the most important thing.', 558, 0), (447466, 'I don''t come from a film background. I haven''t learned anything about films or film-making. But I have a thirst to know everything about my profession. I want to learn about cinematography, about editing, about music recordings, about post-production. So when people in the know talk, I willingly listen.', 71665, 0), (447467, 'I don''t listen to a lot of new stuff. I just like the old stuff. It''s all quite dramatic and atmospheric. You''d have an entire story in song. I never listen to, like, white music - I couldn''t sing you a Zeppelin or Floyd song.', 11891, 0), (447468, 'Perhaps of all the most basic elements of music, rhythm most directly affects our central nervous system.', 70808, 0), (447469, 'I need drama in my life to keep making music.', 392, 0), (447470, 'Music is the voice that tells us that the human race is greater than it knows.', 1702, 0), (447471, 'Michael Jordan changed so much in basketball, he took his power to make a difference. It''s so much going on in music right now and somebody has to make a difference.', 3290, 0), (447472, 'If a composer could say what he had to say in words he would not bother trying to say it in music.', 49246, 0), (447473, 'The man that hath no music in himself, Nor is not moved with concord of sweet sounds, is fit for treasons, stratagems and spoils.', 13, 0), (447474, 'Mozart''s music is so pure and beautiful that I see it as a reflection of the inner beauty of the universe.', 104, 0), (447475, 'It was my 16th birthday - my mom and dad gave me my Goya classical guitar that day. I sat down, wrote this song, and I just knew that that was the only thing I could ever really do - write songs and sing them to people.', 2108, 0), (447476, 'Soul music is true to its name. It''s music that connects to your soul, your spirit. When music resonates with people''s spirit like that, when people can emotionally connect with something or it helps to heal them, transform them, that never goes out of style. People will always need something to relate to.', 68926, 0), (447477, 'I have never denied my background or my culture. I have taught my child to embrace her Mexican heritage, to love my first language, Spanish, to learn about Mexican history, music, folk art, food, and even the Mexican candy I grew up with.', 68376, 0), (447478, 'Just when you think we''re living in a little bit of a divided world, music brings us together.', 68293, 0), (447479, 'Jazz is a white term to define black people. My music is black classical music.', 19782, 0), (447480, 'For my birthday this year, my girlfriends - who knew I''d just inherited my dad''s turntable - gave me a carton of albums like ''Blue Kentucky Girl,'' by Emmylou Harris, and ''Off the Wall,'' by Michael Jackson. It''s all stuff we grew up with. I mean, you can''t have a music collection without Prince''s ''Purple Rain'' - it just can''t be done!', 71666, 0), (447481, 'Opera is the ultimate art form. It has singing and music and drama and dance and emotion and story.', 71667, 0), (447482, 'I would go to sleep with headphones on. My mom and pop - they would have music loud enough to shake the walls.', 68167, 0), (447483, 'Disco is music for dancing, and people will always want to dance.', 70603, 0), (447484, 'I would love to continue in music, with writing... but I am not the kind of person who will hang around if I start to become irrelevant. If that happens, I will bow down gracefully, raise my kids, and have a garden. And I am going to let my hair go gray when I am older. I don''t need to be blonde when I''m 60!', 100, 0), (447485, 'I think I first realized I wanted to be in country music and be an artist when I was 10. And I started dragging my parents to festivals, and fairs, and karaoke contests, and I did that for about a year before I came to Nashville for the first time. I was 11 and I had this demo CD of me singing Dixie Chicks and Leanne Rimes songs.', 100, 0), (447486, 'I definitely try to be myself and not try to imitate other performers. That''s why I got my music degree. I wanted to be prepared and not be a ''product.'' I want people to know that I''m not only a singer but a musician as well. I studied guitar, piano, and composition. I believe that it''s just about being myself on and off stage.', 68293, 0), (447487, 'The standardization of world culture, with local popular or traditional forms driven out or dumbed down to make way for American television, American music, food, clothes and films, has been seen by many as the very heart of globalization.', 47859, 0), (447488, 'Of all noises, I think music is the least disagreeable.', 2087, 0), (447489, 'A big part of making music is the discovery aspect, is the surprise aspect. That''s why I think I''ll always love sampling. Because it involves combining the music fandom: collecting, searching, discovering music history, and artifacts of recording that you may not have known existed and you just kind of unlock parts of your brain, you know?', 71668, 0), (447490, 'The idea of music is to liberate the listener and lead him to a frame where he feels he is elevated.', 66442, 0), (447491, 'Filmmaking is a very complex form - ya know, acting, lighting, screenwriting, storytelling, music, editing - all these things have to come together.', 71669, 0), (447492, 'Music is the medicine of the mind.', 71670, 0), (447493, 'There are more love songs than anything else. If songs could make you do something we''d all love one another.', 1022, 0), (447494, 'My music had roots which I''d dug up from my own childhood, musical roots buried in the darkest soil.', 16427, 0), (447495, 'What is a poet? An unhappy person who conceals profound anguish in his heart but whose lips are so formed that as sighs and cries pass over them they sound like beautiful music.', 3131, 0), (447496, 'Rock music is not meant to be perfect.', 43085, 0), (447497, 'Music is my life, it is a reflection of what I go through.', 68285, 0), (447498, 'I''m very easily distracted unless I have music on. Listening to music while I brainstorm makes me think of scenes that would fit the mood of the music I''m playing.', 184, 0), (447499, 'When wheat is ripening properly, when the wind is blowing across the field, you can hear the beards of the wheat rubbing together. They sound like the pine needles in a forest. It is a sweet, whispering music that once you hear, you never forget.', 28860, 0), (447500, 'Film music should have the same relationship to the film drama that somebody''s piano playing in my living room has on the book I am reading.', 16868, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447501, 'Music is a language, you see, a universal language.', 42348, 0), (447502, 'I definitely shut down sometimes. I always just go into my own little cocoon and write, and I surround myself with as much music as possible. The last girlfriend I had, when we broke up, I remember being in a room for days on days on days with my music cranked up, playing songs like Kanye''s ''808''s & Heartbreak.'' That playlist just was long!', 71671, 0), (447503, 'Music does a lot of things for a lot of people. It''s transporting, for sure. It can take you right back, years back, to the very moment certain things happened in your life. It''s uplifting, it''s encouraging, it''s strengthening.', 67725, 0), (447504, 'I''ve been designing since I was 8. I started sketching dresses I could wear when skating. I was always involved in all aspects of skating, not just the technique, the choreography, the music, but the visual aspects, too - what I should wear.', 66693, 0), (447505, 'Tintinnabulation is an area I sometimes wander into when I am searching for answers - in my life, my music, my work. In my dark hours, I have the certain feeling that everything outside this one thing has no meaning.', 22808, 0), (447506, 'He who joyfully marches to music in rank and file has already earned my contempt. He has been given a large brain by mistake, since for him the spinal cord would suffice.', 104, 0), (447507, 'You have the sun, you have the moon, you have the air that you breathe - and you have the Rolling Stones!', 2466, 0), (447508, 'I don''t care much about music. What I like is sounds.', 65605, 0), (447509, 'When people hear good music, it makes them homesick for something they never had, and never will have.', 13154, 0), (447510, 'As long as my music is real, it''s no limit to how many ears I can grab.', 22894, 0), (447511, 'When you go to a great concert, you feel this arc, almost like the music of a well-chosen set takes you on this trip through emotions and through various forms of intellectual engagement.', 9, 0), (447512, 'I love music of all kinds, but there''s no greater music than the sound of my grandchildren laughing; my kids, too.', 67053, 0), (447513, 'All that stuff about heavy metal and hard rock, I don''t subscribe to any of that. It''s all just music. I mean, the heavy metal from the Seventies sounds nothing like the stuff from the Eighties, and that sounds nothing like the stuff from the Nineties. Who''s to say what is and isn''t a certain type of music?', 43085, 0), (447514, 'I listen to all types of different music. I go to different festivals. I''m around music.', 71672, 0), (447515, 'Classical music requires an immense amount of concentration, and I don''t know if I would''ve been that committed to that particular life.', 71673, 0), (447516, 'As a DJ, people expect a certain sound and a certain danceability for the music. As a producer, I really like to let go of any rules that may exist.', 71674, 0), (447517, 'I think country music is popular - has been popular and will always be popular because I think a lot of real people singing about a lot of real stuff about real people. And it''s simple enough for people to understand it. And we kind of roll with the punches.', 1300, 0), (447518, 'I''m happy to be on a winning team. My individual success, that lasts for a short period of time. The success of being a part of the South, of Atlanta, which is now the hot bed of music, that''s what''s gonna last the longest. The fact that I contributed to planting our flag and moving music to my city, that''s what I''m most proud of.', 48265, 0), (447519, 'Stockholm is unique in that it''s built on islands and surrounded by water, so you get this enormous sense of freedom. It''s got everything you could possibly need - everything New York or London has but without all the people and traffic. It''s also become a very creative city, not only for music but also for fashion and computer games.', 71515, 0), (447520, 'Making words rhyme for a living is one of the great joys of my life... That''s a superpower I''ve been very conscious of developing. I started at the same level as everybody else, and then I just listened to more music and talked to myself until it was an actual superpower I could pull out on special occasions.', 1844, 0), (447521, 'We need to take music out of the ivory tower - both for musicians and for the public. Otherwise, classical music will not survive the 21st century.', 60415, 0), (447522, 'I am a person who thinks about the music first in trying to achieve something musically valid.', 71675, 0), (447523, 'Soul music is timeless.', 558, 0), (447524, 'You can''t fake this music. You might be a great singer or a great musician but, in the need, that''s got nothing to do with it. It''s how you connect to the songs and to the history behind them.', 22852, 0), (447525, 'Music is really driving my whole life.', 52532, 0), (447526, 'The paradox is that I have no love for myself as a human being, but I have immense pride in the music I make, and I believe it has an important place. Others do, too, and the thousands of people with Morrissey tattoos certainly proves something.', 1259, 0), (447527, 'Soul music is about longevity and reaching and touching people on a human level - and that''s never going to get lost.', 70444, 0), (447528, 'My best hostess tip is to have good food and really good music!', 883, 0), (447529, 'Food is one part of the experience. And it has to be somewhere between 50 to 60 percent of the dining experience. But the rest counts as well: The mood, the atmosphere, the music, the feeling, the design, the harmony between what you have on the plate and what surrounds the plate.', 67872, 0), (447530, 'It''s very easy for people to put out music.', 69208, 0), (447531, 'I have a sweet tooth for song and music. This is my Polish sin.', 66871, 0), (447532, 'It''s always been a gift with me, hearing music the way I do. I don''t know where it comes from, it''s just there and I don''t question it.', 19793, 0), (447533, 'It is not the money but the self-respect and wanting to create good music.', 70729, 0), (447534, 'The century of airplanes has a right to its own music.', 22877, 0), (447535, 'That''s my fun time so, to me, doing my homework, studying on what I do, watching the movies, listening to music, all that inspires me so I focus a lot on that and practice.', 67850, 0), (447536, 'If you look at music, you see theme, variation, you see symmetry, asymmetry, you see structure, and these are related to skills in the real world.', 71676, 0), (447537, 'A good compromise, a good piece of legislation, is like a good sentence; or a good piece of music. Everybody can recognize it. They say, ''Huh. It works. It makes sense.''', 1693, 0), (447538, 'This land is your land and this land is my land, sure, but the world is run by those that never listen to music anyway.', 289, 0), (447539, 'I think older people can appreciate my music because I really show my heart when I sing, and it''s not corny. I think I can grow as an artist, and my fans will grow with me.', 957, 0), (447540, 'The basis of our partnership strategy and our partnership approach: We build the social technology. They provide the music.', 5553, 0), (447541, 'Music has always been my protection against the world, from a very young age. I feel safe inside of a jam.', 71484, 0), (447542, 'I''m not a lyric writer to make statements. What I enjoy doing is making paintings with lyrics, creating colorful images. I think that''s more what entertainment and music should be.', 49828, 0), (447543, 'I try to greet my friends with a drink in my hand, a warm smile on my face, and great music in the background, because that''s what gets a dinner party off to a fun start.', 71677, 0), (447544, 'A nation that has no music and no fairytales is a tragedy.', 20064, 0), (447545, 'When you write a play, you work out like a musician on a piece of music. You find all the rhythms and the melody and the harmonies and take them as they come.', 9118, 0), (447546, 'There''s something missing in the music industry today... and it''s music. Songs you hear don''t last, it''s just product fed to you by the industry.', 1429, 0), (447547, 'I have absorbed my life now. I am ready for my music to unfold. I know time flies, but before the end of this year, the album will be out. Even if it kills me.', 71678, 0), (447548, 'Musicians should not play music. Music should play musicians.', 68, 0), (447549, 'People don''t appreciate music any more. They don''t adore it. They don''t buy vinyl and just love it. They love their laptops like their best friend, but they don''t love a record for its sound quality and its artwork.', 25489, 0), (447550, 'Nevertheless the passions, whether violent or not, should never be so expressed as to reach the point of causing disgust; and music, even in situations of the greatest horror, should never be painful to the ear but should flatter and charm it, and thereby always remain music.', 611, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447551, 'We''d like to think that our music will always be bigger than any one of our individual personalities.', 60782, 0), (447552, 'Rock music should be gross: that''s the fun of it. It gets up and drops its trousers.', 68023, 0), (447553, 'I don''t know, my music has always just come from where the wind blew me. Like where I''m at during a particular moment in time.', 21291, 0), (447554, 'How you act, walk, look and talk is all part of Hip Hop culture. And the music is colorless. Hip Hop music is made from Black, brown, yellow, red and white.', 69050, 0), (447555, 'Lean your body forward slightly to support the guitar against your chest, for the poetry of the music should resound in your heart.', 71679, 0), (447556, 'It''s very easy to be cynical about the hall of fame. But on the other hand, it''s really a beautiful thing for someone like me. I dedicated my entire life to this music.', 21291, 0), (447557, 'With so many ways to communicate at our disposal, we must not forget the transformative power of a live music experience and genuine human exchange.', 71680, 0), (447558, 'Personally, I just think rap music is the best thing out there, period. If you look at my deck in my car radio, you''re always going to find a hip-hop tape; that''s all I buy, that''s all I live, that''s all I listen to, that''s all I love.', 392, 0), (447559, 'How to play music may be known. At the commencement of the piece, all the parts should sound together. As it proceeds, they should be in harmony while severally distinct and flowing without break, and thus on to the conclusion.', 819, 0), (447560, 'We should make decisions in life with our hearts, not our brains, not only in music but in daily life.', 68426, 0), (447561, 'There is a sound that comes from gospel music that doesn''t come from anything else. It is a sound of peace. It is a sound of, ''I''m going to make it through all of this.''', 71084, 0), (447562, 'I think in London - and I don''t wanna offend anybody in America, but this is a real statement - they still have the right approach to making music. In the U.S., people see it as a way to make money; they see it as a means to get out. It''s a hustle, which is great - any way you can provide for your family that''s legal is fantastic.', 8650, 0), (447563, 'My liberty is about living. It''s about spreading more love. Even though I was always a peaceful, loving individual, my music sometimes didn''t reflect that. But now it''s different. My music is reflecting the way I feel.', 15440, 0), (447564, 'Music is essentially an emotional language, so you want to feel something from the relationships and build music based on those feelings.', 71681, 0), (447565, 'I try to make music with emotion and integrity. And authenticity. You can feel when something''s authentic, and you can feel when it''s not: you know when someone''s trying to make the club record, or trying to make the girl record, or trying to make the thug record. It''s none of that. It''s just my emotions.', 8650, 0), (447566, 'I suffer from deep depression, so my only release is music.', 71682, 0), (447567, 'For me, music and life are all about style.', 19793, 0), (447568, 'Music''s been around a long time, and there''s going to be music long after Ray Charles is dead. I just want to make my mark, leave something musically good behind. If it''s a big record, that''s the frosting on the cake, but music''s the main meal.', 16427, 0), (447569, 'You walk off the plane in Rio, and your blood temperature goes up. The feel of the wind on your face, the water on your skin, the taste of the food, the music, the sexuality; Brazilians are very comfortable in their sexuality.', 71683, 0), (447570, 'Music is my main goal, but I''m not going to rush a record out. There are so many actors who have come out with albums these days. I don''t want to do it because it''s the thing to do. I want to wait until the time is right.', 3877, 0), (447571, 'For me, music making is the most joyful activity possible, the most perfect expression of any emotion.', 22778, 0), (447572, 'The Internet is both great and terrible. As a source of information, a tool for delivering music and art, it''s great. But spamming ads and piracy of music is terrible. It''s stealing.', 71684, 0), (447573, 'I grew up around salsa, merengue, bachata, bass music, freestyle, hip-hop, techno, house, rave.', 66691, 0), (447574, 'I''ve said that playing the blues is like having to be black twice. Stevie Ray Vaughan missed on both counts, but I never noticed.', 22887, 0), (447575, 'Music, in performance, is a type of sculpture. The air in the performance is sculpted into something.', 1022, 0), (447576, 'When words leave off, music begins.', 1158, 0), (447577, 'All good music resembles something. Good music stirs by its mysterious resemblance to the objects and feelings which motivated it.', 2343, 0), (447578, 'Music is the divine way to tell beautiful, poetic things to the heart.', 19733, 0), (447579, 'Music is forever; music should grow and mature with you, following you right on up until you die.', 1017, 0), (447580, 'Music is well said to be the speech of angels.', 3061, 0), (447581, 'Music has charms to sooth a savage breast, to soften rocks, or bend a knotted oak.', 14081, 0), (447582, 'I see music as fluid architecture.', 16696, 0), (447583, 'The only love affair I have ever had was with music.', 30040, 0), (447584, 'I''ve never missed a gig yet. Music makes people happy, and that''s why I go on doing it - I like to see everybody smile.', 71685, 0), (447585, 'Music is a performance and needs the audience.', 71686, 0), (447586, 'My music, my songs are 100 percent inspired by girl power.', 71687, 0), (447587, 'I don''t make music for eyes. I make music for ears.', 10200, 0), (447588, 'Blues is my life. It''s a true feeling that comes from the heart, not something that just comes out of my mouth. Blues is what I love, and blues is what I always do.', 71688, 0), (447589, 'This will be our reply to violence: to make music more intensely, more beautifully, more devotedly than ever before.', 2229, 0), (447590, 'A musician must make music, an artist must paint, a poet must write, if he is to be ultimately at peace with himself.', 62519, 0), (447591, 'The type of music I make, it''s not just straight-up rapping. There''s emotion in it. That''s why people feel each song differently. I get all my vibes from rock music, you know? All my melodies and all that.', 69206, 0), (447592, 'The blues. It runs through all American music. Somebody bending the note. The other is the two-beat groove. It''s in New Orleans music, it''s in jazz, it''s in country music, it''s in gospel.', 22730, 0), (447593, 'Good fashion is like rock music: all anarchy and revolt.', 57455, 0), (447594, 'The ecstatic insanity of romantic pursuit can be so enhanced by music that entire romantic conquests, victories and ruinous, crushing defeats can be tied to songs to such a degree that it''s almost unbearable to listen to them again, as they bring back the memories so vividly.', 68, 0), (447595, 'Feelings such as loneliness, longing or love are sometimes hard to put into words; maybe that''s why we all love music, because it resonates with something we can''t share.', 71689, 0), (447596, 'People speculate on your personal life all the time anyway. So I just think it''s important to keep my private life private and my public persona more into music, you know?', 12819, 0), (447597, 'Through literacy you can begin to see the universe. Through music you can reach anybody. Between the two there is you, unstoppable.', 64763, 0), (447598, 'Hip-Hop isn''t just music, it is also a spiritual movement of the blacks! You can''t just call Hip-Hop a trend!', 2021, 0), (447599, 'I know what I''ve done for music, but don''t call me a legend. Just call me Miles Davis.', 19793, 0), (447600, 'Motown was about music for all people - white and black, blue and green, cops and the robbers. I was reluctant to have our music alienate anyone.', 66859, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447601, 'When I think of music, I think of music in its totality, complete. From the lowest blues to the highest symphony, you know, so what I''d like to do is exemplify each style of as many periods as I can possibly do.', 71690, 0), (447602, 'I''m inspired by artists and musicians. There are so many wonderful and talented people in the world. I love discovering new music, new writers, or new art.', 558, 0), (447603, 'Our world is enriched when coders and marketers dazzle us with smartphones and tablets, but, by themselves, they are just slabs. It is the music, essays, entertainment and provocations that they access, spawned by the humanities, that animate them - and us.', 47722, 0), (447604, 'Beethoven can write music, thank God, but he can do nothing else on earth.', 1791, 0), (447605, 'May not music be described as the mathematics of the sense, mathematics as music of the reason? The musician feels mathematics, the mathematician thinks music: music the dream, mathematics the working life.', 42089, 0), (447606, 'The end of all good music is to affect the soul.', 71691, 0), (447607, 'Dre was one of my heros in the music industry. If he''s not down for his homeboys, I don''t wanna be a part of him or around him.', 1097, 0), (447608, 'All art constantly aspires towards the condition of music.', 11179, 0), (447609, 'Some people create with words or with music or with a brush and paints. I like to make something beautiful when I run. I like to make people stop and say, ''I''ve never seen anyone run like that before.'' It''s more than just a race, it''s a style. It''s doing something better than anyone else. It''s being creative.', 66900, 0), (447610, 'Music is gathering. Taking our scattered thoughts and senses and coalescing us back into our core. Music is powerful. The first few chords can change us where no self-help books can.', 71692, 0), (447611, 'New Orleans is unlike any city in America. Its cultural diversity is woven into the food, the music, the architecture - even the local superstitions. It''s a sensory experience on all levels and there''s a story lurking around every corner.', 1580, 0), (447612, 'The flame that is naturally clear always gives the most light and heat. If I could blend my talent for poetry and music into one, the light would burn still clearer, and I might go far.', 19830, 0), (447613, 'If something happened where I couldn''t write music anymore, it would kill me. It''s not just a job. It''s not just a hobby. It''s why I get up in the morning.', 22874, 0), (447614, 'Heartbreak was the impetus to me writing poems and music in the first place. Over the years, I had my heart broken so badly that if I didn''t find a way to get all the pain out, I was going to lose my mind. I was crazy! Like, wanting to slash tires and smash car windows. Crazy! I was so hurt that I had to write.', 70444, 0), (447615, 'If you ever go to a music session, you''ll notice that the musicians can sit down and start playing right away, and everyone knows what to do. Of course they''re reading it, but the conductor can tweak little things, and you can take that back to directing motion pictures.', 2269, 0), (447616, 'In Jamaica, them always have throwback riddims, recycled old beats, and the hardcore reggae scene is always present. You have faster stuff like the more commercialized stuff, but you always have that segment of music that is always from the core, from the original root of it.', 70032, 0), (447617, 'One of my favorite places I''ve visited is Havana, Cuba. On my way home from Costa Rica, I did a week in Havana. The colors, the music, the beautiful men and the cars! I love vintage and antique cars and own a couple myself.', 71693, 0), (447618, 'I''m a DJ who makes dance music who got to play with Sting.', 69269, 0), (447619, 'Oratory is the masterful art. Poetry, painting, music, sculpture, architecture please, thrill, inspire - but oratory rules. The orator dominates those who hear him, convinces their reason, controls their judgment, compels their action. For the time being, he is master.', 70968, 0), (447620, 'For me, I actually come from an electronic dance music background: house music, electro house, trance music, even. When I was coming out of school, basically, I discovered Brain Fever, Flying Lotus, J Dilla and all that. That was when I got excited about hip-hop and when the Flume project started.', 71694, 0), (447621, 'I completely love playing and designing games and always will. I am so into games that I listen to game music all day. That may sound strange, but you can guarantee I''m a hardcore gamer and would never let you down by designing a crappy title.', 66842, 0), (447622, 'It takes a real soldier to stay in the music industry and live off the things that have been put before me and be able to survive all this time because it has not been easy.', 71695, 0), (447623, 'Disco music in the ''70s was just a call to go wild and party and dance with no thought or conscience or regard for tomorrow.', 67191, 0), (447624, 'Nothing pleases me more than to go into a room and come out with a piece of music.', 67, 0), (447625, 'I wonder if anyone else has an ear so tuned and sharpened as I have, to detect the music, not of the spheres, but of earth, subtleties of major and minor chord that the wind strikes upon the tree branches. Have you ever heard the earth breathe?', 6587, 0), (447626, 'Rock and Roll: Music for the neck downwards.', 2466, 0), (447627, 'The power of music in Spanish is so strong, that I couldn''t stay away from it any longer.', 65079, 0), (447628, 'I think of a piece of music as something that comes alive when it is being performed, and I feel that my role in the transmission of music is to be its best advocate at that moment.', 25711, 0), (447629, 'Jazz isn''t dead yet. It''s the underpinning of everything in this country. Whether it''s a Broadway show, or fusion, or right on through classical music, if it''s coming out of the U.S., it''s not going to survive unless it''s got some jazz influence.', 64810, 0), (447630, 'There was nothing more I wanted to do than to see my dad react well to my music. I still do. I send him my demos all the time.', 71696, 0), (447631, 'I''m not a fan of anybody music who I feel like a sucka. I don''t listen to you. They play you in the club, you can have the #1 jam, but if I know your character, how can I listen to your music?', 71697, 0), (447632, 'The best music happens when you have a personal connection to it. That same philosophy can extend to the instrument you hold in your hands: if a guitar means something special, you''re bound to do great things with it.', 71698, 0), (447633, 'I love all kinds of art. I mean, I love sketching and acting and music.', 28407, 0), (447634, 'I used to do crazy things that people would bail me out of, and I''m just grateful that I survived. But the music got very lost; I didn''t know where I was going, and I didn''t really care. I was more into just having a good time, and I think it showed.', 3976, 0), (447635, 'A lot of people ask me, ''How did you have the courage to walk up to record labels when you were 12 or 13 and jump right into the music industry?'' It''s because I knew I could never feel the kind of rejection that I felt in middle school. Because in the music industry, if they''re gonna say no to you, at least they''re gonna be polite about it.', 100, 0), (447636, 'The star thing I can live with. The music I can''t live without. And that''s how it lays out for me, you know. I got as big an ego and enjoy the attention.', 2251, 0), (447637, 'I think people are tired of fake music, man. And there''s a lot of it. Technology has reached the point where any boob can walk into a studio and with a little AutoTuning you can have a hit song. I think it''s pathetic.', 1385, 0), (447638, 'Country music has to evolve in order to survive.', 69334, 0), (447639, 'Too many pieces of music finish too long after the end.', 16868, 0), (447640, 'The martial music of every sideburned delinquent on the face of the earth.', 10463, 0), (447641, 'Music conveys moods and images. Even in opera, where plots deal with the structure of destiny, it''s music, not words, that provides power.', 22725, 0), (447642, 'When you work you are a flute through whose heart the whispering of the hours turns to music. Which of you would be a reed, dumb and silent, when all else sings together in unison?', 5542, 0), (447643, 'Music was invented to confirm human loneliness.', 6034, 0), (447644, 'The opera is to music what a bawdy house is to a cathedral.', 411, 0), (447645, 'Music is given to us with the sole purpose of establishing an order in things, including, and particularly, the coordination between man and time.', 16868, 0), (447646, 'Music, I feel, must be emotional first and intellectual second.', 30040, 0), (447647, 'I dare suggest that the composer would do himself and his music an immediate and eventual service by total, resolute and voluntary withdrawal from this public world to one of private performance and electronic media.', 71699, 0), (447648, 'It''s so wonderful... if your whole day is rotten, once they start the music, it seems to melt away.', 71700, 0), (447649, 'The ideal situation would be to bypass all of the drama and mayhem and just get the music right to the people. I''m confident that we''ll eventually figure it out.', 68631, 0), (447650, 'I would like a man now who is rich, and who can give me a boat - a sailboat. I want to own it and let him pay for it. My first love is the sea and water, not music. Music is second.', 19782, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447651, 'Music is a lady that I still love because she gives me the air that I breathe. We need all sorts of nourishment. And music satisfies and nourishes the hunger within ourselves for connection and harmony.', 61043, 0), (447652, 'You''ve seen one of the our gigs you''ve seen ''em all. But if you''re into the music, you''ll know that we played better the night before or we can play better.', 71701, 0), (447653, 'Although technical discussions are interesting to composers, I suspect that the truly magical and spiritual powers of music arise from deeper levels of our psyche.', 70808, 0), (447654, 'There''s so much beautiful music in the world, and the kids are getting robbed.', 71702, 0), (447655, 'Hunting, fishing, drawing, and music occupied my every moment. Cares I knew not, and cared naught about them.', 13434, 0), (447656, 'All old music was modern once, and much more of the music of yesterday already sounds more old-fashioned than works which were written three centuries ago.', 71703, 0), (447657, 'There''s nothing to compare to live music, there just isn''t anything.', 71704, 0), (447658, 'I have music inside me and I''m very lucky to be able to play music and that''s the way that I try to do it.', 67790, 0), (447659, 'So I think it was a good thing It was a little surreal watching Leo scream ''I''m not going to die today!'' with our music playing - that was the last thing on my mind when I wrote the song.', 71705, 0), (447660, 'I take a baths all the time. I''ll put on some music and burn some incense and just sit in the tub and think, Wow, life is great right now.', 71706, 0), (447661, 'I don''t listen to my own music at home.', 25462, 0), (447662, 'There are only two things worth aiming for, good music and a clean conscience.', 71707, 0), (447663, 'What I am looking for... is an immobile movement, something which would be the equivalent of what is called the eloquence of silence, or what St. John of the Cross, I think it was, described with the term ''mute music''.', 19758, 0), (447664, 'I mean, if you turn on the radio, love is 90 percent of the music.', 65079, 0), (447665, 'Coldplay are just four friends trying to make great music.', 71708, 0), (447666, 'The saxophone is a very interesting machine, but I''m more interested in music.', 70833, 0), (447667, 'I''ve never believed that pop music is escapist trash. There''s always a darkness in it, even amidst great pop music.', 70078, 0), (447668, 'My early childhood memories center around this typical American country store and life in a small American town, including 4th of July celebrations marked by fireworks and patriotic music played from a pavilion bandstand.', 70475, 0), (447669, 'My horizon on humanity is enlarged by reading the writers of poems, seeing a painting, listening to some music, some opera, which has nothing at all to do with a volatile human condition or struggle or whatever. It enriches me as a human being.', 6613, 0), (447670, 'The character of instrumental music... lets the emotions radiate and shine in their own character without presuming to display them as real or imaginary representations.', 22699, 0), (447671, 'I may be helping to bring harmony between people through my music.', 638, 0), (447672, 'What does that represent? There was never any question in plastic art, in poetry, in music, of representing anything. It is a matter of making something beautiful, moving, or dramatic - this is by no means the same thing.', 54115, 0), (447673, 'What''s really good is African drum music.', 15776, 0), (447674, 'I write the vocals last, because I wanted to invent the music first and push the music to the level that I had to compete against it.', 71709, 0), (447675, 'There''s a sadness to the human condition that I think music is good for. It gives a counterpoint to the visual beauty, and adds depth to pictures that they wouldn''t have if the music wasn''t there.', 61261, 0), (447676, 'When I was a teenager, I began to settle into school because I''d discovered the extracurricular activities that interested me: music and theater.', 30247, 0), (447677, 'The Bee Gees who are brilliant, I just love great music.', 646, 0), (447678, 'I want to run for the Senate from Tennessee. Not now, but when I''m 50, when music dies down a little bit. I know lots of artists and actors have those delusions of grandeur, but ever since I was a kid, it''s been of interest to me.', 6465, 0), (447679, 'I was king of the mountain for a long time, well, I don''t want that no more. I like to perform every once in a while for people who want to see me, and cut albums of music that is what I''m really about.', 18225, 0), (447680, 'I think you have to keep a childlike quality to play music or make a record.', 9972, 0), (447681, 'It''s the first time I have returned to my roots - like going back to be a trio. The fans really wanted me to go back on stage and do the Supremes music, so I went about trying to make it happen. We''ll go on tour in the summer.', 55180, 0), (447682, 'Punk is not just the sound, the music. Punk is a lifestyle.', 52296, 0), (447683, 'It is piracy, not overt online music stores, which is our main competitor.', 1064, 0), (447684, 'Boy bands should be exploded from a great height. They''re just pretty people singing music written by others.', 2246, 0), (447685, 'Music is my life, professionally, for nearly 60 years. To be recognized by the academy is still the highest honor.', 16427, 0), (447686, 'Music must take rank as the highest of the fine arts - as the one which, more than any other, ministers to the human spirit.', 3690, 0), (447687, 'Those who seek to satisfy the mind of man by hampering it with ceremonies and music and affecting charity and devotion have lost their original nature.', 2480, 0), (447688, 'When you play music with someone who has a heart rather than playing with someone who is just doing it for money or is cynical it makes all the difference.', 70314, 0), (447689, 'Those who have virtue always in their mouths, and neglect it in practice, are like a harp, which emits a sound pleasing to others, while itself is insensible of the music.', 64239, 0), (447690, 'Style has always been very important to us. We grew up in the ''70s. Music was glam rock, punk rock and a very stylish movement.', 71710, 0), (447691, 'I think one of my favorite things to do is just lock myself up in a small room and listen to music and watch films for a day. Also I just like seeing my friends. We have pizza parties which means I get four friends round, we eat a pizza and we''re really lazy and we play PlayStation.', 1593, 0), (447692, 'But with rap music - not just N.W.A. - but rap music in general, seeing these artists wearing these team logos all the time started bringing a synergy and energy about having to rep your city, your team, everywhere and all the time.', 26404, 0), (447693, 'Hip-hop''s always reached out to kids. If you look at the last 10 big albums it might seem ironic. But when I look at the history of this music it''s always had a lot of positivity.', 68084, 0), (447694, 'As long as your intention is pure, and you know what you''re in it for, then you''re alright. And I''m in it because I enjoy it. I take it seriously... real seriously. I mean I could sit and talk all day about the music.', 71484, 0), (447695, 'I''m not trying to pull the rug out from under anybody, but the music really does tell you where to go.', 71484, 0), (447696, 'Music comes from a place we don''t know.', 25529, 0), (447697, 'I was a fan of heavy music - first metal, then punk, then hip hop.', 16828, 0), (447698, 'To really be tortured by a song, it needs to be more than just something you don''t like or don''t get; it has to make your skin crawl by getting under it. Strangely, that last clause could describe provocative or daring music, as well.', 22973, 0), (447699, 'Ironically, being a coach on ''The Voice'' and spending time with those kids, Xenia and Dia especially, I learned a lot about myself. It reminded me how lucky I am that this happened for me, and it kind of lit the spark inside me again for my love of music.', 69334, 0), (447700, 'I want my music to do the explaining.', 271, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447701, 'I feel like music can affect you in so many ways. When you hear a song with a happy melody, it can change your mood; it can change your day.', 69357, 0), (447702, 'Music is part of us, and either ennobles or degrades our behavior.', 3096, 0), (447703, 'Most people live and die with their music still unplayed. They never dare to try.', 10094, 0), (447704, 'I dabbled in things like Howlin'' Wolf, Cream and Led Zeppelin, but when I heard Son House and Robert Johnson, it blew my mind. It was something I''d been missing my whole life. That music made me discard everything else and just get down to the soul and honesty of the blues.', 22686, 0), (447705, 'There is hardly any money interest in art, and music will be there when money is gone.', 12781, 0), (447706, 'There is two kinds of music, the good, and the bad. I play the good kind.', 22681, 0), (447707, 'I was a very interested arts student, I was always into that part of school and when I got into high school I went into architectural drafting. It gave me an understanding of how to build things and it''s really helped me put things in perspective. With my music and my movies, to me it''s all art.', 26404, 0), (447708, 'I can easily say I''ve done everything I''ve wanted in music.', 68483, 0), (447709, 'Music is what I love to do it''s in my veins. ', 271, 0), (447710, 'Music is the wine which inspires one to new generative processes, and I am Bacchus who presses out this glorious wine for mankind and makes them spiritually drunken.', 1791, 0), (447711, 'One and the same thing can at the same time be good, bad, and indifferent, e.g., music is good to the melancholy, bad to those who mourn, and neither good nor bad to the deaf.', 2478, 0), (447712, 'If architecture is frozen music then music must be liquid architecture.', 28763, 0), (447713, 'People often complain that music is too ambiguous, that what they should think when they hear it is so unclear, whereas everyone understands words. With me, it is exactly the opposite, and not only with regard to an entire speech but also with individual words.', 22786, 0), (447714, 'I do know the effect that music still has on me - I''m completely vulnerable to it. I''m seduced by it.', 70074, 0), (447715, 'I found that it wasn''t so oddball to like music and poetry and visual arts, they''re kindred spirits.', 71711, 0), (447716, 'When you write, it''s making a certain kind of music in your head. There''s a rhythm to it, a pulse, and on the whole, I''m writing to that drum rather than the psychological process.', 408, 0), (447717, 'Music is love in search of a word.', 65750, 0), (447718, 'I''ve always felt music is the only way to give an instantaneous moment the feel of slow motion. To romanticise it and glorify it and give it a soundtrack and a rhythm.', 100, 0), (447719, 'For me, a paragraph in a novel is a bit like a line in a poem. It has its own shape, its own music, its own integrity.', 496, 0), (447720, 'The best music is essentially there to provide you something to face the world with.', 2251, 0), (447721, 'Writing has laws of perspective, of light and shade just as painting does, or music. If you are born knowing them, fine. If not, learn them. Then rearrange the rules to suit yourself.', 262, 0), (447722, 'Ever since I was a kid, this was all I wanted to do. I''ve wanted to do music. I wanted to sing. It''s all I know.', 22720, 0), (447723, 'I would like to be known as an ''artist''. Whether that be music, acting, sketching, cooking, whatever. I''m interested in all of those things.', 71712, 0), (447724, 'Mozart''s music is like an X-ray of your soul - it shows what is there, and what isn''t.', 71713, 0), (447725, 'Faith is reason plus revelation, and the revelation part requires one to think with the spirit as well as with the mind. You have to hear the music, not just read the notes on the page.', 10728, 0), (447726, 'Amazingly, I''ve been sort of an anomaly in the music industry. I feel like I''ve been able to exist as kind of a throwback artist.', 7655, 0), (447727, 'If I''m not working on music, I''m usually with my friends playing FIFA. We just kick back - I''m proper chilled.', 70889, 0), (447728, 'I treat every album as a new beginning, so I''m asking myself, ''What is pop music now? What are people consuming?'' and I take these things into effect.', 68293, 0), (447729, 'No two people on earth are alike, and it''s got to be that way in music or it isn''t music.', 9623, 0), (447730, 'I feel like good music comes and goes in waves.', 71714, 0), (447731, 'I don''t live for the accolades. I''m more so about the music. Making it, and putting it out. Those are the two best feelings.', 60269, 0), (447732, 'There''s more to life than listening to rock music.', 56251, 0), (447733, 'When I was a teeny little girl, I was in dancing school, and I sang. We had to put a dance to a song, so I went to the 10-cent store one day and looked at all the sheet music. It was all laid out, and I picked ''Life Is Just a Bowl of Cherries.''', 18677, 0), (447734, 'The rhetoric is the key to the character. It''s the verbal music of the piece.', 1023, 0), (447735, 'The aggressive side of me comes across in my music, but I''m just a sweet girl.', 67650, 0), (447736, 'Music happens to be an art form that transcends language.', 30074, 0), (447737, 'I know that I''m here because of the grace of God. But I also know that I''ve been given this second chance for a specific reason, and that is to bring love to the world again through the voice of my music, and I''m so honored to be able to do it. I''m so blessed that God has chosen me to do that.', 71715, 0), (447738, 'You have to be careful not to make music something you don''t want to do. Which happens. I''ve gotten off the road and been like, ''I hate it. I hate singing, I hate playing guitar.'' Six days later, I''m in my bedroom singing at the top of my lungs because I love it so much.', 69236, 0), (447739, 'With the White Stripes we were trying to trick people into not realising we were playing the blues. We did not want to come off like white kids trying to play black music from 100 years ago so a great way to distract them was by dressing in red, white and black.', 22686, 0), (447740, 'My debut album, ''Forget the World,'' is all about not listening to the negativity around you and to continue to do what you love, no matter what people think. I love what I do. Dance music is my passion, my life. There is no greater feeling than being one with my fans, partying to the music we love.', 69269, 0), (447741, 'I haven''t traveled in Africa nearly as much as I''d like to. I''ve been there a few times, and I''d like to learn more about the various cultures in Africa. But that''s the basis point of where all of the music that I love is based upon, from Africa to Cuba to Puerto Rico to South America.', 65515, 0), (447742, 'There are many singers who have got an exceptional talent, but spend their lives singing in local trains or hotels. Does the country even know who they are? Music in India is restricted only to Bollywood. Whoever manages to make a mark there is remembered. The ones who fail to reach and make it big there are forgotten.', 71716, 0), (447743, 'Music is something that should speak for itself, straight from the heart. It took me a long time to understand that.', 67504, 0), (447744, 'All music is folk music. I ain''t never heard a horse sing a song.', 22681, 0), (447745, 'I had spent many years pursuing excellence, because that is what classical music is all about... Now it was dedicated to freedom, and that was far more important.', 19782, 0), (447746, 'I don''t want to be the cliche American Idol dude. I want to be different, you know - that''s the whole goal, me and music. It''s about being yourself and being unique.', 71717, 0), (447747, 'I discovered after going to music festivals that I am a rock fan. I love the guitars, the phrasing, and the abandon of rock fans.', 1525, 0), (447748, 'Obviously, the cinematography of films is art, just as a still shot can be art. If I''m watching a Wes Anderson movie, the colour palettes alone, and the way they''re painted, could be art. With music, you''re a little bit limited, of course, because it''s only audio.', 22945, 0), (447749, 'Pop music, disco music, and heavy metal music is about shutting out the tensions of life, putting it away.', 71718, 0), (447750, 'To me, the greatest pleasure of writing is not what it''s about, but the inner music that words make.', 262, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447751, 'I went to see ''Phantom of the Opera'' with my grandma and my mom when I was very little. The stage, the voice, the music... Composer Andrew Lloyd Webber has been a massive inspiration to me for some time - the storytelling, that deliciously somber undertone in his music.', 47, 0), (447752, 'I love to have a bath with beautiful, relaxing music on and have no rush to do anything. It''s a wonderful indulgence, and it helps me to calm down and stop my mind running overtime.', 70709, 0), (447753, '''Cat?'' ''Cat'' can be anybody from the guy in the gutter to a lawyer, doctor, the biggest man to the lowest man, but if he''s in there with a good heart and enjoy the same music together, he''s a cat.', 22681, 0), (447754, 'I have three siblings. My sister makes music. My older brother is a classical conductor, and my younger brother is a mixing engineer.', 8136, 0), (447755, 'Any real record person knows that the number one most powerful marketing tool when it comes to music is repetition.', 66669, 0), (447756, 'I love to read. I love to stretch. In the morning, I get up, and if I''m not in a hurry, I will lie on the floor on a rug, look through some books and magazines, and maybe listen to music and try to do stretching exercises to tune up.', 2152, 0), (447757, 'Country music is the people''s music. It just speaks about real life and about truth and it tells things how they really are.', 70235, 0), (447758, 'If I hadn''t had music in my life, it''s quite possible I''d be dead and I''d much rather be alive.', 13043, 0), (447759, 'But I''ve been freestyling and messing around with rhyming since I was 13. That''s when I really started listening to hip-hop music.', 38715, 0), (447760, 'A great song is a great song, whether it''s on vinyl or CD or cassette or reel to reel or mp3. Then again, that might be an overly optimistic view, but I do think that great music will transcend the medium in which it is delivered.', 67002, 0), (447761, 'Music is a thing that changes people''s lives. It has the capacity to make young people''s lives better.', 13014, 0), (447762, 'I''m free from holding personal anger because I can express what I want through my music.', 1121, 0), (447763, 'Going to college and studying music is not a bad idea at all. I don''t know if you can go to college and be taught heart.', 69334, 0), (447764, 'I love singing jazz. I don''t like the idea that classical music should be over here and jazz should be someplace else. It''s all wonderful, and we should be open to enjoying it all.', 65864, 0), (447765, 'Is Wagner a human being at all? Is he not rather a disease? He contaminates everything he touches - he has made music sick.', 11, 0), (447766, 'Only in country music can you compare an old pickup truck and an old guitar to your wife and turn it into a love song... Thank God for country music.', 69345, 0), (447767, 'There are times pop music is the end result when I''m in the studio, but I don''t really go in and say, ''Today I am going to make a pop song,'' but it can happen.', 70208, 0), (447768, 'I could compare my music to white light which contains all colours. Only a prism can divide the colours and make them appear this prism could be the spirit of the listener. ', 22808, 0), (447769, 'The best, most beautiful, and most perfect way that we have of expressing a sweet concord of mind to each other is by music.', 4080, 0), (447770, 'Music is what I breathe, what I love to do. It keeps me alive.', 682, 0), (447771, 'It''s all about music, because music is basically what''s... been my avenue out of maybe being involved in things I shouldn''t be.', 66691, 0), (447772, 'I see music as one language. If one musical form eats its own tail, it dies. So it needs to be a mongrel, it needs to be hybridised.', 9151, 0), (447773, 'Same with anyone who''s been flying for years and loves it still... we''re part of a world we deeply love. Just as musicians feel about scores and melodies, dancers about the steps and flow of music, so we''re one with the principle of flight, the magic of being aloft in the wind!', 424, 0), (447774, 'I became inspired while I was listening to music on the radio. I felt the music in my head sounded better, so I turned off the radio and scribbled it down on a piece of paper. I remember that it was in May. People liked that song. They said it was beautiful. I felt overjoyed.', 67338, 0), (447775, 'The truest expression of a people is in its dances and its music. Bodies never lie.', 56815, 0), (447776, 'Music, Rock and Roll music especially, is such a generational thing. Each generation must have their own music, I had my own in my generation, you have yours, everyone I know has their own generation.', 27500, 0), (447777, 'Music at times is more like perfume than mathematics.', 48563, 0), (447778, 'He has Van Gogh''s ear for music.', 22666, 0), (447779, 'Everywhere in the world, music enhances a hall, with one exception: Carnegie Hall enhances the music.', 71713, 0), (447780, 'I love being in public places, but I can''t stand long, drawn-out music festivals.', 71719, 0), (447781, 'I don''t feel guilty about the music I love. If you feel guilty about something you dig, then you should stop feeling guilty about it. One of my favorite albums to this day is the 10th anniversary ensemble cast of ''Les Miserables,'' the ultimate cast recording, and it is still something I love listening to top to bottom.', 1385, 0), (447782, 'I like music that''s more offensive. I like it to sound like nails on a blackboard, get me wild.', 22869, 0), (447783, 'The music industry can make you feel like a prostitute.', 55158, 0), (447784, 'Well, we like to let down our hair and pep it up at the dances, but we keep it slower when we broadcast. We have to please everybody, and that softer music appeals to the larger amount of people. It''s like eating too much cake. You have to have your steak too.', 71720, 0), (447785, 'My music, I feel, has always been experimental, but it had got to a point where I felt disconnected from it completely. I didn''t want to be a Clark Kent/Superman: I couldn''t really say, ''Well, B.o.B''s the old me, and Bobby Ray''s the new me.'' I had to just make a point.', 71721, 0), (447786, 'You know, I do music. If you look under the hood of the industry I''m in, it''s all based on technology. From radio to phonographs to CDs, it''s all technology. Microphones, reel-to-reels, cameras, editing, chips, it''s all technology.', 32686, 0), (447787, 'When I hear music that parents hate, or older musicians hate, I know that''s the new music. When I hear older people saying, ''I hate Rap or Techno'' I rush to it.', 56386, 0), (447788, 'I want to be ripped apart by music. I want it to be something that feeds and replenishes, or that totally sucks the life out of you. I want to be dashed against the rocks.', 3572, 0), (447789, 'I do so much music that it''s like a fog, and I can''t even remember all of it.', 71722, 0), (447790, 'I began observing, making paintings of my surroundings, taking a vow of silence, listening, composing music, writing, and making time for formal education. Then I started telling stories.', 71723, 0), (447791, 'Sonnymoon and Quadrants are a couple of bands that really inspire me in terms of the melodics of things and certain tones and just what feels good. It takes me back to the type of music that I grew up on in my household. We played a lot of gangsta rap, but we also played a lot of oldies, and I think that mix is part of what inspires my sound.', 22894, 0), (447792, 'I made numerous attempts to find a way to do it all, to be a creative singer, songwriter, producer, and to be the mother, daughter, sister, lover, wife. And the thing about music is, with me, that she''s a harsh mistress. She does not come to me in the midst of stress.', 12437, 0), (447793, 'I find that music makes people just sit and listen, firstly. Then, they seem to interpret their own emotions with the music and it makes them ponder their own life a lot. And then they start to question: Am I happy in my work? Am I happy in my relationships? What am I striving for?', 70718, 0), (447794, 'The ''Carousel'' overture has always been one of my all-time favorite pieces of music.', 68033, 0), (447795, 'I would like to see more African-American singers as part of our opera companies. If you take music and the arts out of the public schools, then you''re going to lose a lot of people that you might have discovered were talented, very early.', 65864, 0), (447796, 'I love to act and put on a show, but you''re playing a character all the time. For music, it''s really just me being myself.', 69218, 0), (447797, 'The language of film is further and further away from the language of theater and is closer to music. It''s abstract but still narrative.', 71724, 0), (447798, 'The world of classical music is so fascinating. It''s a world that encompasses people from everywhere and erases the basic restraints of nationality everyone is united by this common language of music. ', 67800, 0), (447799, 'I didn''t know that there were many rules in music when I first started writing.', 69250, 0), (447800, 'If you took away all pain, if everyone lived forever, everything would be bland, flat and boring; there would be no reason for art, music, newspapers, love because we would all be in a mono state of happiness.', 10448, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447801, 'The way you pronounce words the Puerto Rico way, it''s not really global for music. Colombians speak some of the best Spanish in the world. So having a Colombian next to me every time I write makes my music more international.', 70736, 0), (447802, 'Getting to make the music, and having a good time doing it, is the most important thing to us.', 69350, 0), (447803, 'It is so characteristic, that just when the mechanics of reproduction are so vastly improved, there are fewer and fewer people who know how the music should be played.', 1163, 0), (447804, 'The principle of the endless melody is the perpetual becoming of a music that never had any reason for starting, any more than it has any reason for ending.', 16868, 0), (447805, 'I''m not trying to overcome my father or fill his shoes or reach any kind of level that he did. We''re talking about a Mozart of rock music.', 68887, 0), (447806, 'But however measurable, there is much more life in music than mathematics or logic ever dreamed of.', 48563, 0), (447807, 'No one had ever told me that whites were supposed to sing one kind of music and blacks another - I sang what I liked in the only voice I had.', 22803, 0), (447808, 'The reflection of the world is blues, that''s where that part of the music is at. Then you got this other kind of music that''s tryin'' to come around.', 92, 0), (447809, 'The movie that''s had the most effect on me is Jaws. To this day when I''m in the ocean, I''m hearing that music.', 68304, 0), (447810, 'The only thing that I miss lately in all music is somebody that will put out a melody that you can whistle. It doesn''t seem like there''s anything happening like that.', 64134, 0), (447811, 'I painted the picture, and in the colors the rhythm of the music quivers. I painted the colors I saw.', 7791, 0), (447812, 'Jazz is the only music in which the same note can be played night after night but differently each time.', 50908, 0), (447813, 'I want to make music that will make the blood surge in your veins, music that will get people up and dance.', 71725, 0), (447814, 'I was influenced when I was younger by the cartoon movies that Disney put out, like Cinderella and what not. I watched those movies over and over when I was younger and the music is ingrained into my head. Nowadays, I''m still humming the tunes. It taught me the fundamentals.', 68410, 0), (447815, 'People always accuse me of being motivational in a way, like it was a bad thing, but that''s just how I was raised. My mom raised me in a positive environment, with lots of love in my heart, and that reflects in my music.', 68285, 0), (447816, 'I''m really an inner spirit that only makes itself known through the music. A lot of people think I''m an introvert, or quiet and moody. I''ve even heard some people say that there''s a certain mystery or darkness about me. I''m not that way. I''m just really into what I do.', 71726, 0), (447817, 'Trance is a very emotional and uplifting form of dance music. It appeals to many people in this way having such a strong connection with emotions. It makes people happy and ready to party.', 69210, 0), (447818, 'A name doesn''t make the music. It''s just called that to differentiate it from other types of music.', 71655, 0), (447819, 'Until I realized that rock music was my connection to the rest of the human race, I felt like I was dying, for some reason, and I didn''t know why.', 2251, 0), (447820, 'DJs are in incredible competition, musically. And they are the most musically creative and sensitive people in all the music charts. I am amazed how they are.', 1121, 0), (447821, 'Music is a whole oasis in my head. The creation process is so personal and fulfilling.', 3877, 0), (447822, 'Music is the tool to express life - and all that makes a difference.', 30074, 0), (447823, 'I do listen to other music though, and try to pick up what is good.', 71727, 0), (447824, 'But in the next world I shan''t be doing music, with all the striving and disappointments. I shall be being it.', 62567, 0), (447825, 'No good opera plot can be sensible, for people do not sing when they are feeling sensible.', 219, 0), (447826, 'You know, all my songs are relatives, brothers, sisters, cousins.', 70998, 0), (447827, 'R&B is the one thing that has influenced every kind of music. Every artist that there is, from those that are sung the most to Adele - you know, she was so influenced by so many R&B artists and soul music - it''s clear in her writing that that''s where it comes from.', 69046, 0), (447828, 'Love cannot express the idea of music, while music may give an idea of love.', 7846, 0), (447829, 'For me, the backdrop of half the experiences of life includes music.', 64661, 0), (447830, 'Half the battle is selling music, not singing it. It''s the image, not what you sing.', 44554, 0), (447831, 'But recently I began to feel that maybe I wouldn''t be able to do what I want to do and need to do with American musicians, who are imprisoned behind these bars; music''s got these bars and measures you know.', 42348, 0), (447832, 'The music industry is saying, This is the format, and if you''ll fit into this format, you can be on radio, and if radio will play you, MTV will expose you, and MTV will expose you, we''ll sell records.', 1197, 0), (447833, 'I hate most of what constitutes rock music, which is basically middle-aged crap.', 9151, 0), (447834, 'Most people wouldn''t know music if it came up and bit them on the ass.', 1022, 0), (447835, 'What is this? It''s music to get a brain seizure by.', 43085, 0), (447836, 'There are certain things in which mediocrity is not to be endured, such as poetry, music, painting, public speaking.', 5879, 0), (447837, 'Music, as many people have said, is the universal language. Of course points are made which make you think about things, but ultimately it makes you feel. And that''s why people remember more songs that have meant something during their life than films. They start to define periods in your life, and that''s kind of the beauty of it.', 66351, 0), (447838, 'My whole thing is not just to play music for people, but to make them part of the evening.', 71728, 0), (447839, 'Before breaking into music, I had various jobs: forklift driver, driving a courier. But I was forced into working rather than doing it off my own bat because that was my dad''s way: you got a job and paid your way.', 67085, 0), (447840, 'I start really missing London when I go away. I have a little flat, but very central. I live above a pub and you''d think it''d be a nightmare, but I like hearing the music and it''s quite comforting.', 16756, 0), (447841, 'Now is now, and I live everything one day at a time. The fact that I''m still on the planet and able to still make music is such a miracle.', 66767, 0), (447842, 'If you invent something, you''re doing a creative act. It''s like writing a novel or composing music. You put your heart and soul into it, and money. It''s years of your life, it''s your house remortgaged, huge emotional investment and financial investment.', 11508, 0), (447843, 'I''m not necessarily that big of a clubbing junkie, but I really like dance music as a genre.', 71729, 0), (447844, 'I don''t need an award to inspire me to keep making music.', 71730, 0), (447845, 'I find a therapy in playing music, in many different ways.', 67345, 0), (447846, 'We''re all just animals. That''s all we are, and everything else is just an elaborate justification of our instincts. That''s where music comes from. And romantic poetry. And bad novels.', 9555, 0), (447847, 'The music industry is dominated by guys. I work with men 98 percent of the time - producers, arrangers, musicians, engineers.', 67847, 0), (447848, 'Everyone one-on-one will be completely honest about the music that they listen to. But then you get into a group situation, and then it''s the cool/uncool debate. I have really done my very best to reinforce the very fact that your heart knows better than your head does what you like when it comes to music and what not.', 1385, 0), (447849, 'I always tell the fans, ''Screw it! Like what you like. Listen to what you want.'' Insisting that one type of music is better than the next is snobbery, and I have no time for that. Check out all the music that''s out there. There''s great stuff you''re probably missing.', 1385, 0), (447850, 'In country music, one of the ways we may have gone wrong in the past is trying to be politically correct all the time.', 69334, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447851, 'As humans, we have the tendency to call on God only when we think that we''re in dire straits as opposed to cultivating a real relationship with Him every day. And that''s what my music tries to convey to all the listeners - try to cultivate it every day.', 71084, 0), (447852, 'If you believe in what you do and you really want to be in music, just stick at it. It''s always a learning process. Enjoy it because I think making music is a privilege, really. In an ideal world, it should also always be fun. As much as possible, make it fun.', 69934, 0), (447853, 'Life seems terrible and disappointing, so you need to find something you need to make you stick around. Music that makes me happiest is the saddest music, with the most emotional feel.', 69994, 0), (447854, 'It''s hard to dance to really fast music. All you can do is pump your fist to it, and after a while, you''re going to have a seizure.', 71444, 0), (447855, 'My mother was American, and my father was from the Caribbean, and there was a big open door into the world of humanity and music.', 71731, 0), (447856, 'Making music is an emotional thing. And when you''re on a video shoot with 50 people there, you have to somehow, in a non-emotional way, say what you want and not feel guilty for it. And that takes growing up and that takes... not caring how people perceive you as much. And it just takes experience, I think.', 69251, 0), (447857, 'From the first album, Led Zeppelin was always going to be a totally new approach from what had gone before - whether it was approaching the blues or folk music like ''Babe I''m Gonna Leave You'': nothing existed like that.', 20029, 0), (447858, 'When I began making electronic music, the only thing I was thinking about was creating music that I really liked. I didn''t think about what effect it would have; I was busy doing it.', 66933, 0), (447859, 'I love a lot of different styles, but my heart belongs in electronic music.', 67046, 0), (447860, 'I can''t create music if I''m wearing a mask and not being myself, and that was the problem with The Czars.', 67046, 0), (447861, 'A song without music is a lot like H2 without the O.', 61038, 0), (447862, 'Music and silence combine strongly because music is done with silence, and silence is full of music.', 22725, 0), (447863, 'For the introduction of a new kind of music must be shunned as imperiling the whole state since styles of music are never disturbed without affecting the most important political institutions. ', 51, 0), (447864, 'The music industry is a strange combination of having real and intangible assets: pop bands are brand names in themselves, and at a given stage in their careers their name alone can practically gaurantee hit records.', 5248, 0), (447865, 'There''s no religion but sex and music.', 9151, 0), (447866, 'Music makes me high on stage, and that''s the truth. It''s like being almost addicted to music.', 92, 0), (447867, 'I see architecture not as Gropius did, as a moral venture, as truth, but as invention, in the same way that poetry or music or painting is invention.', 40310, 0), (447868, 'I love music passionately. And because I love it I try to free it from barren traditions that stifle it.', 22877, 0), (447869, 'I firmly disbelieve that one has to be a tortured soul to write good music.', 67582, 0), (447870, 'It''s nice to be able to backtrack and not be embarrassed by the music you used to listen to.', 71732, 0), (447871, 'I''m saddened to see that everyone''s pitched out the baby with the bath, in that we say that it can''t be one or the other, it could be both. I mean, just because we listen to classical music doesn''t mean that we can''t listen to jazz.', 68526, 0), (447872, 'Change is always happening. That''s one of the wonderful things about jazz music.', 71733, 0), (447873, 'The tango is really a combination of many cultures, though it eventually became the national music of Argentina.', 25711, 0), (447874, 'Playing sport was somewhat frivolous, but I liked it. I rebelled a little bit, and wouldn''t go to music lessons and things like that, but I would go and play ball. My parents learned to love it because they saw how much I got out of it.', 67885, 0), (447875, 'We do play to our audience. It''s very important. You can''t create music in a vacuum.', 68301, 0), (447876, 'The beautiful thing about hip-hop is it''s like an audio collage. You can take any form of music and do it in a hip-hop way and it''ll be a hip-hop song. That''s the only music you can do that with.', 57363, 0), (447877, 'One of the interesting things here is that the people who should be shaping the future are politicians. But the political framework itself is so dead and closed that people look to other sources, like artists, because art and music allow people a certain freedom.', 70078, 0), (447878, 'I don''t like to talk about things where you''re going to gt one side or the other unhappy. My music has no politics.', 28482, 0), (447879, 'I do promotion when it is necessary, but I always want to get back to the music.', 70718, 0), (447880, 'If you pour some music on whatever''s wrong, it''ll sure help out.', 44212, 0), (447881, 'Music - that''s been my education. There''s not a day that goes by that I take it for granted.', 52296, 0), (447882, 'I like music because it''s the only invisible art form.', 68887, 0), (447883, 'People think our music''s very aggressive or angry or whatever, and it''s just the opposite, really... I like laughing. And I like being really calm before a show, and smiley.', 12800, 0), (447884, 'If the pressure is getting to you, whistle. In a barely audible way. It''s the best way I know of to let go of tension. Music gets your mind off the situation, and the act of whistling melts the tension out of your body.', 67580, 0), (447885, 'It was amazing and inspiring to see so many people come together through music to aid the great state of Vermont.', 71484, 0), (447886, 'There are a lot of influences from different countries in my music. For example, I chose the guitar in my music, I think that it is a feminine instrument, so when I do not sing, the music expresses my voice.', 71687, 0), (447887, 'As a woman, you spend so much time either cooking or getting ready to go somewhere. I like to have music when I''m doing either of these things.', 71191, 0), (447888, 'I believe that music is another form of news. Music is another form of journalism to me so I have to cover all the areas with my album.', 2080, 0), (447889, 'Many people die with their music still in them. Why is this so? Too often it is because they are always getting ready to live. Before they know it, time runs out.', 24754, 0), (447890, 'Develop interest in life as you see it; in people, things, literature, music - the world is so rich, simply throbbing with rich treasures, beautiful souls and interesting people. Forget yourself.', 497, 0), (447891, 'Medicine to produce health must examine disease; and music, to create harmony must investigate discord.', 4891, 0), (447892, 'A lot of pop music is about stealing pocket money from children.', 55255, 0), (447893, 'I was about sixteen when I discovered that music could get you laid, so I got into music boy, didn''t matter what you looked like either, you could be a geeky looking guy but if you played music, whoa, you''d get the girls.', 71577, 0), (447894, 'As Erykah Badu, it has nothing to do with me, the way I look, my hair wrap, my style, it''s about you and what you feel for my music. If I can make you feel like the way that people who influenced me made me feel, that''s completion.', 964, 0), (447895, 'I mean, just because you''re a musician doesn''t mean all your ideas are about music. So every once in a while I get an idea about plumbing, I get an idea about city government, and they come the way they come.', 8258, 0), (447896, 'Music is always a commentary on society.', 1022, 0), (447897, 'I believe music should reflect yourself in some way and not just yourself at the given time. I feel that when you die or when you''re going, someone''s supposed to listen to that music and know everything about you. And I just try to get that across.', 2080, 0), (447898, 'I love electronic music, and I love drum and bass.', 69263, 0), (447899, 'In its beginnings, music was merely chamber music, meant to be listened to in a small space by a small audience.', 49246, 0), (447900, 'Music is intended and designed for sentient beings that have hopes and purposes and emotions.', 9596, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (447901, 'Music is God''s gift to man, the only art of Heaven given to earth, the only art of earth we take to Heaven.', 8764, 0), (447902, 'Music is the soundtrack of your life.', 22689, 0), (447903, 'Every song is like a painting.', 68433, 0), (447904, 'The advice I am giving always to all my students is above all to study the music profoundly... music is like the ocean, and the instruments are little or bigger islands, very beautiful for the flowers and trees.', 71679, 0), (447905, 'I need music. It''s like my heartbeat, so to speak. It keeps me going no matter what''s going on - bad games, press, whatever!', 11158, 0), (447906, 'The tuba is certainly the most intestinal of instruments, the very lower bowel of music.', 2274, 0), (447907, 'I alone of English writers have consciously set myself to make music out of what I may call the sound of sense.', 35, 0), (447908, 'My loathings are simple: stupidity, oppression, crime, cruelty, soft music.', 76, 0), (447909, 'When a singer truly feels and experiences what the music is all about, the words will automatically ring true.', 71734, 0), (447910, 'There are so many opportunities in life, that the loss of two or three capabilities is not necessarily debilitating. A handicap can give you the opportunity to focus more on art, writing, or music.', 13145, 0), (447911, 'To be alive, to be able to see, to walk, to have houses, music, paintings - it''s all a miracle. I have adopted the technique of living life miracle to miracle.', 2523, 0), (447912, 'A verbal art like poetry is reflective; it stops to think. Music is immediate, it goes on to become.', 219, 0), (447913, 'To know how to suggest is the great art of teaching. To attain it we must be able to guess what will interest; we must learn to read the childish soul as we might a piece of music. Then, by simply changing the key, we keep up the attraction and vary the song.', 4754, 0), (447914, 'If one plays good music, people don''t listen and if one plays bad music people don''t talk.', 40, 0), (447915, 'Country music is three chords and the truth.', 71735, 0), (447916, 'Music has to be written while people are still excited about a particular melodic or rhythmic sequence. The idea doesn''t come out the same if we''re not really excited about it.', 5945, 0), (447917, 'When they look back on me I want ''em to remember me not for all my wives, although I''ve had a few, and certainly not for any mansions or high livin'' money I made and spent. I want ''em to remember me simply for my music.', 3401, 0), (447918, 'There was one man who was interested in the color of music, the connection between light and music, and that was Einstein.', 71736, 0), (447919, 'In serial music, the series itself is seldom audible... What I''m interested in is a compositional process and a sounding music that are one in the same thing.', 71737, 0), (447920, 'I discovered that the most interesting music of all was made by simply lining the loops in unison, and letting them slowly shift out of phase with other.', 71737, 0), (447921, 'Rock n'' Roll came from the slaves singing gospel in the fields. Their lives were hell and they used music to lift out of it, to take them away. That''s what rock n'' roll should do - take you to a better place.', 7252, 0), (447922, 'My dad wanted me to play when I was a kid, so I learned to play the guitar. I pursued a career in music because I love it so much and I enjoy what it does to those who hear it.', 71304, 0), (447923, 'I cannot conceive of music that expresses absolutely nothing.', 41392, 0), (447924, 'I was never worried that synthesizers would replace musicians. First of all, you have to be a musician in order to make music with a synthesizer.', 70128, 0), (447925, 'Good rock music always tends to be around.', 70790, 0), (447926, 'My free time at home is usually spent emailing, listening to music, reading and talking on the phone. I wish I was on the phone less, but I have been fortunate to stay in touch with so many incredible friends.', 30680, 0), (447927, 'If I know you''re very good in music, I can predict with just about zero accuracy whether you''re going to be good or bad in other things.', 11453, 0), (447928, 'In ''thinking up'' music I usually have some kind of a brass band with wings on it in back of my mind.', 48571, 0), (447929, 'My goal is to be one with the music. I just dedicate my whole life to this art.', 92, 0), (447930, 'I mean, there''s times to rock and roll, and I love that too. But I think my first love is acoustic music.', 71738, 0), (447931, 'Music is the expression of the movement of the waters, the play of curves described by changing breezes.', 22877, 0), (447932, 'It''s about the music and that''s it. I''m not an entertainer. But I do entertain people, see what I mean?', 71701, 0), (447933, 'Music is one of those things that is constantly going in my head all the time. It''s sort of like the evolution and creation of doing food, or my philosophy about wine. It''s always beating in my head, so it keeps the spirit moving.', 69277, 0), (447934, 'Yes, there are times when I get extremely depressed and how I sublimate those feelings is through music.', 68500, 0), (447935, 'Unfortunately, the young generation, who I believe have their own place in the sun like I had mine; but I wish it was possible there were other ways to have them understand this music was here before they came, and the reason that it was here.', 71739, 0), (447936, 'I have been tied up with music for about as long as I can remember. By the time I was four I was picking out little tunes my mother played on the reed organ in the living-room.', 71740, 0), (447937, 'If you already have a piece of music ingrained in your body, why would you not play it?', 71741, 0), (447938, 'I can write music but I''m not much for words.', 71742, 0), (447939, 'I am musical and I enjoy theatre, but I never wanted to just do theatre. I always wanted to go into film. I love film. I loved growing up in the theatre, but I always wanted to do film all along. But, I still pursue music separately.', 71743, 0), (447940, 'But anyone who knows anything about the music industry knows it''s not only about the music.', 69350, 0), (447941, 'In music you have people exposing this very vulnerable part of themselves, and you also have the lifestyle is so fast that oftentimes people search for whatever the easiest way to feel relaxed in the midst of all of it, or the easiest way to have energy.', 71660, 0), (447942, 'I come from a background of experimental music which mingled real sounds together with musical sounds.', 71744, 0), (447943, 'They told me that they are starting a classic label, and wanted me to be the first artist. So I signed, and am producing myself, and writing my own music, but I''m their first artist on their classic label. And I have creative control.', 71745, 0), (447944, 'When I was younger, I was in love with everything about the British Isles, from British folklore to Celtic music. That was always where my passions were as a young girl, and so I studied folklore as a college student in England and Ireland.', 9872, 0), (447945, 'We just make music. For I never stop working.', 53555, 0), (447946, 'Instrumental music can spread the international language.', 71746, 0), (447947, 'Music has always been transnational; people pick up whatever interests them, and certainly a lot of classical music has absorbed influences from all over the world.', 25711, 0), (447948, 'The real reason we ended up getting into that type of music was our dad worked for an oil company so we spent a year overseas when we were young kids. Because of that, it was all Spanish TV and radio so we ended up having these ''50s and ''60s tapes, tapes of that music.', 69280, 0), (447949, 'Like Jermaine was saying, it''s a beautiful day, and we''re just glad all of this is behind us. We can go on with our lives. And Michael can go on with his life and do what he does best, and that''s making good music, making his fans happy, people happy all over the world.', 71747, 0), (447950, 'I use music as a medium to talk to people.', 42348, 0);
