hotography, and writing.', 52964, 0), (447962, 'Music is all about wanting to be better at it.', 67087, 0), (447963, 'Someone who knows only music, understands nothing about it.', 71749, 0), (447964, 'There''s an awful lot of resources that can be drawn upon in an improvised music concert.', 66834, 0), (447965, 'Curtain! Fast music! Light! Ready for the last finale! Great! The show looks good, the show looks good!', 71750, 0), (447966, 'If a professional musician in a symphony orchestra is playing Beethoven. But this particular orchestra have played this particular chestnut so many times, they can play it in their sleep. Does the genius remain present in the music or not?', 22657, 0), (447967, 'I quit high school on my birthday. It was my senior year and I didn''t see the point. This was 1962, and I was ready to make music.', 71751, 0), (447968, 'Music is like a huge release of tension.', 68940, 0), (447969, 'I don''t like to be labeled, to be anything. I''ve made the mistake before myself of labeling my music, but it''s counter-productive.', 1082, 0), (447970, 'My head works in music, so there''s always music there.', 12803, 0), (447971, 'So, when you divide the world into music lovers, music fans and then those people who are just very casual about their music, it''s wallpaper to them, it''s elevator music, it''s just the thing that''s playing in the background that helps them through their day.', 48866, 0), (447972, 'Beyond a certain point, the music isn''t mine anymore. It''s yours.', 11398, 0), (447973, 'There''s definitely an old school element to my music, but I also think it''s modern.', 68285, 0), (447974, 'Grammys, American Music Awards, successful albums, I''d pick my kids any day over any of it.', 960, 0), (447975, 'Have you listened to the radio lately? Have you heard the canned, frozen and processed product being dished up to the world as American popular music today?', 1502, 0), (447976, 'Don''t make music for some vast, unseen audience or market or r